title: gone!!!
directions: Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Line pan with saltine crackers, salt side up.
Melt margarine with sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over saltines; spread evenly.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Spread with a knife as chips melt.
Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate for several hours.
Break into pieces for serving. Enjoy!

title: crock-pot oyster stew
directions: Put all ingredients except oysters in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high 1 1/2 hours.
Stir well.
Add oysters and cook on low for 1 to 3 hours.
Sprinkle with cayenne and serve hot.

title: millionaires
directions: Mix caramels and evaporated milk in top of double boiler. Melt.
Take off stove.
Add pecans.
Stir well.
Drop onto cookie sheet greased with butter.
Cool.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until cold.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add remaining ingredients.
Store in glass containers in refrigerator 2 or 3 days.
Add a 2 liter bottle of 7-Up when serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix lime juice, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Blend in food coloring.
Fold into pie shell.
Let sit until firm.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and allow to sit for flavors to meld.
Use as a dip for any fresh fruit.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, saute the onion in butter until tender. Add flour. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken broth and cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, cream, basil, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add the vegetables and cook gently until heated thoroughly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. Excellent.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix in Accent, salt, onion and lemon juice to the chicken, celery, almonds and mayonnaise.
Toss and place in baking dish. Top with Velveeta cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated.

title: chicken picante
directions: Coat chicken with bread crumbs, brown lightly in oil over medium heat in heavy skillet and mix liquids and seasonings.
Add vegetables to skillet and pour liquid-seasonings mixture over top. Cover tightly and cook over medium-low heat until chicken is done, about 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: condensed milk
directions: Pour ingredients into blender and beat 1 minute.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Add oleo to hot noodles and mix.
Add other ingredients.
Put in greased large 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 45 minutes more.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, in mixing bowl.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 300° until firm in the center.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Cook and drain meat and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Add milk, soups, 1/3 of cheese and mashed chilies; bring to a boil.
Be careful; it will stick.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together egg, milk and shortening.
Mix dry ingredients, add mixed liquids and beat until smooth.
Bake in 9-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: low cholesterol ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in freezer can.
Finish filling with 2% milk.
Freeze as usual.

title: cabbage bake
directions: Brown meat and seasonings.
Wash rice, chop cabbage and mix everything together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Open and stir after cooking 45 minutes.
Recover and continue cooking.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat chicken and well drained pineapple in double boiler 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in mayonnaise.
Heat 5 minutes longer.
Stir in celery and 1/3 cup almonds.
Spoon into serving dish.
Sprinkle with remaining almonds and green pepper. Garnish with watercress and spiced apple rings.
Serve at once. Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/4 c. cooking oil in pan and heat while mixing ingredients.

title: my favorite dip
directions: Layer in 9 x 12 pan. Bake at 400° until cheese melts. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix tomatoes and salt.
Let stand about 12 hours.
Drain. Heat vinegar, sugars and spices to a boil; add sliced onions and boil gently 5 minutes.
Add the drained tomatoes and peppers; bring slowly to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon.
Pack into hot jars.
Be sure syrup covers vegetables.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 5 minutes.
Remove jars and complete seals unless closures are self sealing type.
Makes 9 half pints.

title: hamburger on a half bun
directions: Mix all ingredients into raw meat.
Spread to edges of open-faced buns.
Broil until meat is done.

title: pickled bologna
directions: Pound round steak (not with flour).
Trim and cut in strips. On strip, sprinkle flour, salt and pepper.
Add diced onion, diced green pepper and a strip of bacon.
Roll up; secure with a toothpick.
Bake, covered with a small amount of water, at 350°. Baste occasionally.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.

title: zucchini milano
directions: Remove casing from sausage; crumble meat.
Saute in medium size frying pan 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Pour off drippings, then measure 1 tablespoon and return to pan.
Stir in zucchini and onion; saute 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, garlic salt, oregano and pepper.
Place sausage on top; cover.
Cook slowly 15 minutes or until zucchini is slightly tender.
Serves 6.

title: mexi-corn lasagna
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large skillet. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Combine cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese, oregano and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Arrange 6 tortillas on bottom and sides of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, overlapping as necessary. Top with half the meat mixture. Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Arrange remaining tortillas over cheese. Top with remaining meat mixture. Bake in preheated 375° oven about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Remove from oven; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving with additional picante sauce. Serves 8.

title: hearty green pea soup
directions: Wash peas.
Drain.
Add 2 qts. water to peas, season to taste.
Cook 2 hours add potatoes, carrots, onions, herbs, and butter.
Simmer until vegetables are tender and soup is to desired thickness.
Can add ham bits or smoked sausage, etc., if desired.

title: chicken-turkey casserole
directions: Mix
well.
Leave
in
refrigerator overnight in mixing bowl. Next
day,	put in containers to be baked.	This may be baked at once or kept frozen up to six weeks.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump truck cake
directions: Pour pineapple chunks and juice into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spoon cherry pie filling on next.
Shake entire box of cake mix on and spread evenly.
Cut butter into slices and spread over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: grandma's raisin crunchies
directions: Mix baking powder, soda, vanilla and Raisin Bran.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in coconut and raisins, then add flour and salt to butter mixture; mix well. Stir in Raisin Bran mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes; watch carefully, bottoms burn quickly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: skillet german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender; peel and dice.
Keep warm.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Pour off all but 4 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Blend in soup, milk, relish, vinegar and salt.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil. Gently stir in potatoes and all but 1 tablespoon of bacon.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle bacon on top and garlic with wedges of hard-boiled egg.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Line bottom of tube pan with waxed paper.
Grease and flour pan.
Sprinkle pecans over bottom of pan.
In a small bowl, combine granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into 6 pieces.
Roll biscuits in sugar/cinnamon mixture and stack evenly in pan.
Pour melted butter evenly over top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.
Combine powdered sugar and enough milk to make thin enough to drizzle over cake.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Combine all ingredients well with an electric mixer. Store in an airtight container and keep refrigerated. Yields about 16 oz.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Mix first four ingredients in deep baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy fruit waldorf
directions: Drain fruit cocktail well and mix lightly with celery and walnuts.
Serve on salad greens and top with Cream Dressing or mayonnaise.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar in 1 cup of water and salt to taste. Bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Remove boiling mixture.
Add gelatin and onion and cool. Combine remaining ingredients and add to liquid.
Put in molds and chill.
Serve on lettuce with a teaspoon of mayonnaise on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Add sugar to pie filling. Stir in marshmallows and allow to stand 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Before serving, cut up and add drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.

title: apple bagel snack
directions: Place bagel on broiler tray.
Top with American cheese, then place a slice of apple on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Toast in oven for a few minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: crab meat mold
directions: In
a medium saucepan, combine soup, cheese and onions. Heat until
cheese
is
melted.	Blend in mayonnaise.
Remove from heat.
In
another pan, sprinkle gelatin over water over low heat; stir until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in soup mixture. Add crab meat and celery.
Pour into a 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate 6
hours or overnight.	Unmold on serving plate.
Serve as spread with crackers.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook bacon well.
Drain most of the fat.
Add tomato sauce and parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Beat eggs in a cup.
Boil spaghetti in salted water (al dente).
Drain spaghetti and pour back in hot pan.
Pour eggs on spaghetti and toss.
Add sauce, Parmesan cheese and pine nuts.
Toss and serve.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix and pack into glass pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: carolyn's fluffy blueberry muffin
directions: Mix all ingredients until moistened.
Fold berries into mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: tupperware bread
directions: Mix together and use part of flour to knead but use all 10 cups.
Put in Tupperware bowl (the large one!), burp and let rise until it pops off.
Make into loaves, let rise and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup with milk or wine; stir well.
Spoon evenly over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: Brown meat with onion and mushrooms.
Drain. Cook noodles. Drain.
Put in large pan with tablespoon butter or vegetable oil. Add meat mixture and Ragu.
Mix.
Put cheese on top.
Put in oven for 1 hour at 300° or until done.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms and saute until tender.
Add 1 cup water, chicken base, pepper and sherry, then simmer.
Blend cornstarch and water until smooth.
Add to sauce while stirring and cook until thickened.
Turn off heat. Stir in yogurt and chicken strips.
Serve over rice or noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Crumble hamburger meat over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onion flakes next. Pour cans of soup over that; then pour peas.
Cover with Tater Tots. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Blend flour into creamed mixture. Stir in baking bits, raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough about 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix together well and pour into raw dough shell.
Cook in a medium oven until brown.
Cool.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients and stir until sugar dissolves. Pour over cucumbers, pepper and onions.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: western bean casserole
directions: Cut bacon in pieces; saute with onion and hamburg until meat is lightly browned.
Add all the rest and stir.
Bake at 350°. Serves 12.

title: gone-all-day-stew
directions: Mix together soup, water, wine and flour until smooth. Combine remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired.
Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread.
Yields 8 servings.
Has 10 gm fat and 103 mg. cholesterol.

title: filled pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides and place in shallow baking dish. Lightly mix bread cubes, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and seasonings; place a mound of filling in each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water and pour over chops and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: very strawberry pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add ice cubes and stir until melted.
Prepare instant pudding with 3/4 cup milk as directed on package for pie.
Let stand about 2 minutes.
Blend in gelatin.
Chill if necessary until thickened.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip and strawberries.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.

title: angel-lemon delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup of the sugar, a little
at	a
time,
beating
after each addition.
Put egg yolks in top of double boiler.
Beat until thick.
Add remaining 3/4 cup
of sugar, lemon juice and peel to the egg yolks. Cook	over boiling
water until thick, stirring occasionally. Soften gelatin in the 1/4 cup of water and then add to the egg yolk-lemon mixture.
Cool.
Fold in egg white mixture, using a rubber spatula.
Put
half
of
the
angel
cake crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour	half
of
the
sauce
over
cake.
Repeat layers. Let
stand
in
refrigerator
overnight.
Cut
into squares.
Top each with a dollop of whipped topping.

title: "miss" lonnie mae's peach foam salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk together, then mix with cooled jello-pineapple mixture.
Pour into long Pyrex dish and chill for several hours until set.

title: joanne's pineapple banana bread
directions: Stir well with spoon.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add liquid.
Put frying chicken in baking pan or casserole dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and cover with lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove lid and turn heat to 500° for 15 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: peanut butterscotch squares
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; stir in flour.
It is crumbly. Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add vanilla and beat 1 minute.
Add eggs one at a time and beat 1 minute after each.
Fold in dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: 3 cheese chicken
directions: Cook 1/2 cup chopped onions and green pepper.
Stir in cream of chicken soup, milk, drained mushrooms, chopped pimento and basil.
Pour 1/2 noodles in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 sauce, cottage cheese, chicken, American cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat twice.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on platter.
Spoon salsa onto cream cheese until cream cheese is covered.
Cover salsa with a generous layer of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle onion, green pepper, tomato, black olives and jalapeno peppers over the cheese layer.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: Put a wafer in bottom of cupcake paper.
Beat rest of ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into each paper until thickness desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.
Top with melted chocolate chips, drizzled on top or favorite topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Only add cold water to cover beans.
Add approximately 1 tablespoon baking soda.
Cover and bring to boil. It will be very foamy.
Remove from heat and rinse under cold water.
(This supposedly removes some gas from the beans.)
Cover again with cold water (only cover, no more).
Add cut up onion, cut up bacon, salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to boil, then simmer until beans are soft, but not mushy (water should be almost absorbed).
Add molasses, dry mustard and brown sugar to taste. Pour into baking dish.
Lay bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Arrange whole eggs and sliced onion rings in alternate layers in a large glass jar with tight fitting lid.
Combine in saucepan the vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Pour over eggs and seal jar.
(Make sure eggs are covered.)
Store jar in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days before serving.
Serve with buttered popcorn, crackers or pretzels.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together well, then drop by spoon in hot grease.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer all ingredients in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in order listed.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving. Serve warm or cool and, if desired, with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: clam chowder(makes 5 cups)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine milks and remaining ingredients and stir together for 10 minutes or until thick and bubbly.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in Dutch oven at 300° for 3 1/2 hours or until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Let cool.
Chop or dice tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add salt and mayonnaise.
Stir just until mixed well and refrigerate. Serves 10 to 12.

title: wilma's skillet hash
directions: Heat Crisco oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add potatoes, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook on medium heat, turning occasionally, until potatoes are tender.
Add broth, meat, salt, hot pepper sauce and pepper to taste.
Cook until meat is hot. Makes 8 servings.
Contains 230 calories, fat 9 g (81 cal or 35% of total calories), sat fat 2 g (9% of total calories), carb 15 g, protein 22 g, chol 60 mg and sodium 100 mg.

title: tex-mex stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Brown meat with garlic in oil; drain off fat.

title: archie's chocolate pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and cocoa thoroughly.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk.
Add egg yolks.
Stir well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup milk to cocoa mixture.
Stir over medium heat about 5 minutes, until mixture thickens.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Beat well.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour pork spareribs
directions: Brown pork slightly in hot oil.
Add water, cover and cook slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over cooked pork and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks and let cook only 2 or 3 minutes.
Can double recipe.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Blend ingredients in order listed; add enough milk to finish filling freezer.

title: date candy
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, egg yolks and dates.
Cook in skillet for 10 minutes, stirring as you cook.
Remove from heat and add the nuts and Rice Krispies. Stir well.
Pour coconut on wax paper.
Drop by spoonful and roll in coconut.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix and
sift
dry
ingredients;
sift
twice.
Work in lard with
tips of fingers.
Add milk gradually.
Mix in with knife
to a soft dough.
It will drop without spreading.
Drop by
spoonfuls on buttered pan, 1-inch apart.
Brush over with milk and brown in hot oven 8 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo; mix into eggs.
Add corn bread mix; blend well. Add all other ingredients; pour into iron skillet and bake 35 minutes or until brown at 375°.

title: pasta with basil, plum tomatoes and garlic(for one person)
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil and cook pasta.
Heat olive oil on medium heat in a pan.
Add garlic, basil and tomatoes.
Cook until tomatoes soften slightly.
Add lemon juice and pasta.
Toss lightly.
Top with cheese.
Make yourself a tossed salad.
Yummy!

title: wild rice salad
directions: Rinse rice under cold running water.
Bring 3 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add salt to taste.
Add rice.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 minutes.
(After 20 minutes, taste every 5 minutes.
Rice grains should pop open to reveal the white insides but should not turn mushy.)

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set 1 hour.
Drain off and add sugar, vinegar, celery seed and turmeric.
Boil 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and Bisquick thoroughly.
Add grated cheese and mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls (about the size of a jack ball).
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: creamed diced carrots with green pepper
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan over moderate heat.
Add onion and carrots; stir.
Cover, lower heat, and cook for 10 minutes.
Add green pepper, cover and cook for 2 minutes. Sprinkle in flour, stir, then add half and half, broth and seasonings.
Stir well.
Bring the mixture to simmer, stirring constantly, then cover and cook over low heat for 4 to 5 minutes, until the carrots are done.
They should be slightly crunchy.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Chop onion, carrot, bell pepper and cucumber very fine.
Mix with cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Salt to taste.
Use as a sandwich spread.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Combine 8 medium Russet potatoes (boiled, peeled and cubed) with 1 cup of sliced celery and chopped red onion.
Combine the salad dressing mix with mayonnaise and water.
Add to potatoes and toss to coat.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef potato boats
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper and celery (all chopped) in 1 ounce vegetable oil.
Drain fat.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Cut potatoes lengthwise in half.
Scoop out and reserve potato shells.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup hot water.
Add to cake mix and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, pineapple and cornstarch.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat and fold in egg whites.
Cool slightly and put into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let yeast sit while preparing other ingredients.
Heat buttermilk until warm.
Remove milk from heat and combine with oil, sugar and salt.
Sift flour and soda in a large bowl.
Mix yeast with buttermilk mixture, then add in flour mixture.
Mix well and let stand for 10 minutes.
Roll out dough on floured surface and cut out biscuits.
Place rolls in a pan with melted butter.
Coat each side with butter.
Let rolls stand 30 minutes in a warm place to rise.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Dice crab meat and mix in a bowl with chopped celery, 2 diced hard-boiled eggs, seasoning and salad dressing.
Mix well. Serve as an appetizer or as a salad on lettuce.
Garnish with parsley or paprika.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Add grated zucchini and stir.
Mix together flour and other ingredients. Add raisins and nuts to dry ingredients. Stir into zucchini mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: barbecue meat loaf with ground turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine 3 tablespoons barbecue sauce and water.
Add oats, egg, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and salt; mix well.
Add turkey, bell pepper, onion, corn and chilies, if desired; mix well.
Pat into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes; spread top of loaf with remaining barbecue sauce during last 10 minutes of cooking.
Meat loaf is cooked through when it springs back to touch.
Serve warm or cold, with additional barbecue sauce, if desired.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Use enough water from potatoes to make mixture soft. Mix and pour in casserole dish.

title: peach nut bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour mixture into pans and bake 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pans 5 minutes before turning out to finish cooling.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix butter cake mix, butter and egg by hand and press in baking dish.
Beat cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar until creamy.
Pour over first mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over hot cake when baked.
Cool.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour over casserole and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Add water to spices in a saucepan, stirring 2 minutes. Add butter and melt. Add brown sugar and vanilla. Stir 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Use 2 tablespoons butter batter (more or less to taste). Add 1 jigger rum and stir. Fill mug with boiling water and stir. Store remainder of butter batter in refrigerator.

title: granny's better than snuff cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box using milk instead of water.
Bake in an oblong pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bring to boil the pineapple and sugar.
When cake is done, remove from oven.
Punch holes in it and pour pineapple mixture over it.
Let set awhile. Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Add the pudding into mixer bowl and combine with cream cheese.
Spread over cooled cake.
Cover cake with a layer of sliced bananas and then cover with Cool Whip.
Decorate top with strawberry halves and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: heavenly dip
directions: For the mountain, this should be doubled.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.

title: friendly recipe
directions: One Tongue that doesn't slander.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a saucepan, blend mustard with a little vinegar.
Add remaining vinegar and next 6 ingredients.
Cover, heat to boiling, simmering 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over onions and eggs.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight.

title: impossible quiche tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 18 big muffin cups.
Beat first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Spoon 2 tablespoons in each cup.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon over batter in each cup.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pineapple fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir well.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients.
Add to dry mixture. Mix until just moist.
Fry a few at a time in 2 to 3-inches oil.

title: hash brown potatoesfort morgan, colorado
directions: Thaw hash browns, squeeze out excess moisture.
Melt butter. Mix with soup, sour cream.
Add onions and cheese.
Add hash browns.
Pour mixture into large baking pan.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and beat thoroughly.
Pour into bottles or jars for storing.

title: creamed eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients. Heat thoroughly. Serve over toast. Serves four.

title: fig muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in fig preserves. Spoon batter into greased and floured muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gina's tater tot casserole
directions: Brown
ground beef; drain.
Mix with next 3 ingredients in large casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Make scrambled eggs, using the eggs and milk.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Fry bacon.
Drain and crumble over eggs. Spread sour cream over all.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: mother's favorite peach custard pie
directions: Slice peaches into unbaked pie shell.
Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add all other ingredients, including melted butter, and pour over peaches.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 50 to 60 minutes.
This pie is best served warm. Makes 5 to 6 generous portions.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, cook onion until tender; add flour and broth until thickened.
Take off the burner.	Stir in sour cream and set aside.
In mixing bowl, mix 2 cups of sauce, chopped chicken, one cup of cheese, chilies and cumin.
Soften tortillas according to package directions, then place equal portions of the filling mixture (chicken) in each tortilla and arrange in 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce on top of the tortillas and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Grease pie plate (20 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix apples and spices; turn into plate.
Beat remaining ingredients, except streusel, until smooth (15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with mixer).
Pour into plate over apples.
Sprinkle with streusel.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean (55 to 60 minutes).

title: cup of gravy
directions: Dissolve cornstarch and bouillon cubes in cold water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until boiling and smooth.

title: green rice
directions: Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Saute onions in butter.
Add rice, broccoli, egg mixture and cheese.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: In frying pan, add ground chuck, salt and pepper.
Cook until well done.
Rinse with hot water and drain.
Boil egg noodles, rinse with hot water and drain.
In large saucepan slowly cook tomatoes, tomato sauce, green peppers and onion.
Combine ground chuck and noodles for a very appetizing dish.
Serve piping hot with cheese sprinkled on top.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and continue to beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in a mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: marinated black-eyed peas
directions: Drain Bush's Best black-eyed peas.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Add chopped celery and onion.
Combine oil, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and cayenne; mix well.
Pour over peas.
Stir gently.
Allow to chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
At serving time, add the diced tomato.
Mix carefully.
Serve as a relish with meats, or garnish with lettuce and a spoonful of mayonnaise and serve as a salad.

title: 1000 island salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: gingerbread
directions: Dip bread into eggs and milk.
Put on a hot pan on stove until brown.
Put syrup and cinnamon and powdered sugar on top.
Eat!

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a 15 x 10-inch baking dish, sprayed with nonstick spray, dip chicken in melted Parkay spread and coat each piece with remaining ingredients.
Put in dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until tender.
Serves 6.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa and salt in 4 to 6-quart saucepan. Heat milk in microwave until hot but not boiling. Gradually add to cocoa mixture, stirring until well blended. Stir in vanilla.

title: big batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well. Add chips and nuts. Chill.
Make into balls or spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: double chocolate cupcakes(quick and light)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Add water and next 4 ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir just until batter is moistened.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon into foil or paper-lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then sprinkle 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put in crock-pot frozen, cold or whatever, cook on high, stirring occasionally until melted.
Then turn on low.
Cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Can be doubled or up to four times recipe.
Real good for potlucks!

title: bul-ko-kee(korean barbecue beef)
directions: Trim fat from beef and cut diagonally across the grain into 1/8-inch slices.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in beef until coated.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes; drain beef. Stir-fry until light brown over medium heat, 2 to 3 minutes. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Mix together and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir often for it sticks easily; do not let it scorch.
Pack hot into sterilized pint jars. Process in hot water bath for 30 minutes.
Use as you would crushed pineapple.

title: cheese date balls
directions: Have cheese and margarine at room temperature; blend well. Mix in seasonings well and cut in flour (best by hand).
Chill dough.
Stuff a date with a pecan half and form cheese dough around each date.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mix in a blender and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake for 15 minutes more.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in chocolate (melted and cooled); add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 5 minutes after each addition.
Turn into cooled baked pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Graham cracker crust can also be used.

title: cheese apple bake
directions: Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Put drained apples in dish. Cream butter and Velveeta.
Add sugar and flour.
Put mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, toss together the graham cracker crumbs and the melted butter.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a small mixing bowl, beat the remaining 1/2 cup of butter, about 30 seconds, until softened.
Add powdered sugar, beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Spread mixture over crumb mixture.
Slice bananas lengthwise into halves and arrange over egg mixture.
Spoon pineapple over bananas.

title: angel cornbread (yeast)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Pour into well greased pan or skillet and bake at 450° until done.
You can use one 11-inch skillet or two 8-inch skillets.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight. Drain beans.
Add pork or melted bouillon cube and 2 quarts water. Boil for 2 minutes.
Cover; lower heat and simmer for 1 hour until beans are barely tender.
Add remaining ingredients until veggies are tender.
Serves 6.

title: sirloin steaks with blue cheese butter
directions: Trim excess fat.
Place on grill 4 inches from hot coals. Sear 3-5 minutes.
Turn steaks after cooking to your liking. Lightly score surface of steak.
Combine remaining ingredients. Spread steaks with blue cheese butter.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Pour olive oil over day old bread.
Cut in cubes and spread on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle oregano and parsley over top.
Bake at 300° until light golden brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in a 5 or 6 quart Dutch oven.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add green pepper, onion, garlic, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer until tender.
Add salsa.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Pour meat mixture over rice in Dutch oven.
Stir and heat through.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and cocoa in a saucepan. Bring to a boil for about 1 minute. Add peanut butter. Mix well. Add oatmeal. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: cranberry star salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add pineapple syrup and chill until partially set.
Add cranberry mixture, pineapple, walnuts and celery.
Pour into star mold or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Serve plain or with a dab of mayo.

title: fried squash patties
directions: Slice squash; place in pan with onion, salt, pepper and small amount of grease.
Smother and cook until almost all the water is cooked out.
Take off stove and drain as well as possible.
Add egg and enough flour to make a thick mixture.
With hands, make small patties and fry in small amount of grease until done.
If needed, roll patty in small amount of flour, then fry.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: In large skillet, cook meat and onion until the meat is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.	Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green onion and green pepper.
Spread half of noodles in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 pan; top with a little of meat sauce. Cover with cheese mixture. Add remaining noodles and meat sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add margarine (softened), eggs, vanilla and bananas.
Add nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat slightly.
Add remaining 1/2 cup milk, last 2 cups flour, baking powder and extracts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Put into cold oven and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine in a small bowl the sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Cut each biscuit in 1/4ths and roll each piece in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Put in Bundt cake pan or angel food cake pan.

title: beef loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add ground beef, eggs, onion, salt, pepper and sage.
Mix well.
Form into loaf and place in greased loaf pan.
With fork, rough top of loaf.
Combine brown sugar, catsup or chili sauce, nutmeg and ground mustard.
Pour over loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: golden graham's s'mores
directions: Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Heat corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips to boiling point in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal in large bowl; toss until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, one cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand until firm, at least 1 hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature no longer than 2 days.
Makes 24 squares.

title: winter day bean soup
directions: Combine the last 7 ingredients in a soup pot; boil 10 minutes. In the meantime, saute the first 5 ingredients until onion is clear.
Add to soup pot.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over toasted French bread.

title: ozelma's cheese diablo(appetizers)
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Add cayenne pepper and grated cheese. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
These are very hot.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk; mix thoroughly.
Blend in remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: hot christmas wassail
directions: Combine fruit juices and cider.
Combine spices and tie in cloth bag.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.

title: mexican coffee
directions: Whip whipping cream with 1/2 teaspoon each of nutmeg and cinnamon.
Spice coffee with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sweeten to taste.
Serve demi-tasse with generous spoonful of the whipped cream.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Combine beef, potato and cabbage in large microwave casserole. Cover and microwave on High for 7 minutes or until beef is no longer pink; stir once.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and microwave 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once during cooking time.

title: whoopie pie icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on whoopie pies.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Place approximately 10 pieces of chicken in pan.
Put on salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: caramelicious fudge brownies
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, melt the caramels with the milk; stir until smooth.
Immediately after removing brownies from oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Drizzle with caramel.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: strawberry summer cake
directions: Stir together the jam and Cool Whip.
Cut angel food cake into 3 layers.
Spread the Cool Whip/jam mixture on the cake.
Put in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: fresh summer tart
directions: Press cookie dough onto greased 14-inch pizza pan and bake according to package directions.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 4 tablespoons of the frozen orange juice until fluffy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit decoratively on crust.
Cut in wedges.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: peach strawberry soup
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients except lemon slices and mint.
Cover and chill about 2 hours.
To serve, put 1/2 cup into 5 bowls and garnish with lemon slices and mint sprigs.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream butter and sugars until fluffy. Add egg and mix well. Add salad oil and vanilla, mixing well. Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well. Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Flatten with fork dipped in water. Bake 12 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing. Makes 7 dozen.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in Bundt pan at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: grandma mag's banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Grease loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth, scraping down sides of blender as necessary.
Place in a serving bowl.
Cover and chill before serving.
Serve as a dip with fresh vegetables or chips.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut up in small pieces when cool. Cut up celery in small pieces. Mix all ingredients. Keep refrigerated. Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crush graham crackers and vanilla wafers.
Chop cherries and nuts.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Pack in covered container and store in refrigerator.
Slice and serve.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in 7-Up; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: creamy swiss salad
directions: Combine salad greens, cheese, olives and eggs in a large salad bowl.
Blend mayonnaise, cream, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over greens and toss.
If desired, garnish with tomato wedges. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add soda to sour cream, then blend with creamed mixture.
Beat eggs well and add, then add mashed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together, then mix into first mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Blend well and turn into greased and floured loaf tins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 large loaves.

title: apple brown crisp
directions: Put on stove and heat.
Pour in baking dish.

title: meat and oyster dressing
directions: Put meat to fry.
Meanwhile, grind next 5 ingredients and add to meat as it is ground.
Let fry until it comes to grease on top. Skim grease. Add oysters and cook until oysters are done. Add bread crumbs and season to taste.
May need more bread crumbs to make right consistency.
Use own judgement.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well and roll into 3 small rolls.
Wrap well in waxed paper and freeze.
Remove from freezer and slice into 1/8-inch slices.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Heat cheese and butter on low heat until melted or microwave for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cocoa, vanilla, powdered sugar and nuts. Mix well.
Mixture will be very thick.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
No cooking and very delicious.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Arrange vanilla wafers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with about 1/4-inch Cool Whip.
Top with more vanilla wafers, then more Cool Whip, ending with wafers.
Chill overnight.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Melt chocolate
bits
and allow to cool.
Cream butter, sugar and
vanilla until fluffy; add syrup and continue creaming.
Beat in
eggs and chocolate.
Sift flour; sift together dry ingredients.
Stir
into batter.
Fold in chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Spread
in
a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; bake in a
moderate
oven about 25 minutes.
Cut in bars when cool.

title: banana macadamia nut (or walnut) bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, eggs, baking soda, salt, orange peel and vanilla.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes. Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue beating, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 1 minute.
By hand, stir in coconut and nuts.
(Batter will be thick.)
Spread into 1 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 3 greased 5 1/2 x 3-inch mini loaf pans.
Bake 9 x 5-inch loaf for 60 to 65 minutes or mini loaves for 35 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Slowly add
cranberry
juice to sugar.	Stir well.
Add pineapple juice and chill.	Pour into bowl and add ginger ale. Makes 32 punch cup servings.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Place all ingredients except dumplings in dutch oven; cover double with water. Cover with lid. Cook over medium high until boiling and chicken is done, no pink remains; and vegetables are tender. While chicken is cooking, make dumplings. Drop dumpling batter by tbsp onto bubbling stew. Cover tightly, reduce heat. Cook 12-15 min. without lifting cover. 8 servings.

title: crock-pot peanut clusters
directions: Melt all candy in crock-pot on high (about 1/2 hour).
After melted, unplug and add peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Sets up in a short time.
Freeze well.

title: apple pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet or shallow pan.
Remove 2 tablespoons butter and set aside.
Put the apple slices in a large bowl with lemon juice.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Toss to coat slices.
Cook the apples over medium heat in skillet with melted butter, stirring often, until apples are tender but still hold their shape.

title: venison stew
directions: Thoroughly brown venison in fat hot, turning often.
Add water, beef broth, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion and seasonings.
Cover; simmer (don't boil) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cover partially and cook until tender.
Thicken liquid for gravy, if desired.

title: german pancakes
directions: Heat butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven.
Blend other ingredients in blender.
Pour in hot pan and cook 25 minutes.

title: nell hughes' sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease tube pan. Add a little batter, then sprinkle some pecan mixture over this.
Add a little more batter and some more pecan mixture, until it is all used up. Bake at 350°.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Arrange bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer Cheddar cheese, Swiss cheese and bacon over bread.
Beat eggs with milk and salt in bowl.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
May chill overnight before baking.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order listed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: chile-sausage squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise; stir well.
Spread mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage and onion in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well between paper towels.
Layer sausage mixture over biscuit mixture.
Combine egg, cheese, remaining mayonnaise and chiles; spread over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings or about 40 appetizers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, eggs, cheese and crackers (save some for top) all together.
Add 1 cup hot milk over mixture.
Top with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips, and pour into casserole. Sprinkle garlic chips over casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven until hot.
Don't overcook as mayonnaise will separate.
Serves 8.

title: don's shrimp, cashew and rice fry
directions: Prepare the rice according to the box directions, set aside. Heat the oil and soy sauce in a large skillet.
Saute the cashews, mushrooms and water chestnuts until hot.
Add shrimp and heat well. Mix in the rice and heat until the liquid is absorbed.
Serve with egg rolls and Hardee's garden salad.

title: manwich pockets(great for kids and parties)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cup pan for 10.
Prepare Manwich Sloppy Joe sauce as directed.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each greased muffin cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides, forming 1/4-inch rim.
Spoon Manwich sauce (about 1/4 cup) into each biscuit-lined cup.
Cut cheese slices in half.
Crisscross cheese slices on top each cup.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges of biscuits are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from pan.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add raw potatoes and onion; cook until potatoes are partly done.
Add tomato juice.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: aunt judy's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups very warm water.
Stir in sugar and oil until sugar is dissolved.
Mix in flour.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Put sugar, tomato sauce and mustard in bowl; set aside.
Mix beef, onion, crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce mixture and stir until well mixed.
Put in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over meat.
Cook on High for 18 to 20 minutes or until done in microwave.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick chili
directions: In a saucepan, brown the ground beef; drain.
Add soup, beans and chili powder.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add water if a thinner soup is desired.

title: party wienies
directions: Mix and simmer over low heat for about 2 hours.

title: chicken
directions: Marinate boneless chicken breast in above mixture. Then cook until chicken is tender.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer all ingredients, except Doritos, corn chips, etc., mixing sour cream, taco seasoning and mayonnaise for second layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with Doritos, corn chips, etc.

title: pepper and cabbage relish
directions: Put tomatoes, cabbage and salt through food chopper.
Place in a cloth bag and drain overnight.
Next morning, put peppers and onions through chopper.
Mix vinegar, brown sugar, cinnamon, black pepper and celery seed in large pot, then add all chopped vegetables and bring to a boil.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix all together and put in casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot.

title: elizabeth's fudge
directions: Melt butter in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk and sugar.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches the medium soft ball stage.
Once this temperature is reached, maintain boiling for a minimum of 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add chocolate and stir until chocolate melts.
Add marshmallow cream and stir until blended. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and set overnight.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Beat egg with water slightly.
Add vinegar.
Mix into flour-shortening mixture. Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes 5 (9-inch) single crusts.
May be frozen in pie dishes.
Place waxed paper between covers in plastic bags for freezing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash fruit carefully in colander.
Let sugar and water come to a boil.
Add lemons, figs and spices, tied in a bag.
Boil slowly until figs are tender and clear, about 1 hour.
Lift fruit carefully into sterilized jars; cover with juice.
Seal while hot. Yields 4 pints.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix (minus the reserved cake mix) and press into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan (use metal, not glass).

title: caribbean jerk chicken
directions: *Scotch bonnet peppers range from red and orange to yellow green.
Shaped like a Scotchman's bonnet, they are the preferred island pepper and very hot.
They usually can be found only in Hispanic markets in the Milwaukee area.
Jalapeno or Serrano peppers may be substituted.

title: chop suey
directions: In Dutch oven or large covered skillet, saute beef and pork until well browned.
Add onions, celery and bean sprouts; water can be added for plenty of moisture.
Place in slow oven (300° to 325°) for about an hour.
Add soy sauce.
If necessary, thicken with cornstarch.
Pour over rice and top with Chinese noodles.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli and drain.
Do not rinse.
Put in airtight container.
Add Accent, lemon juice and oil.
Toss lightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 30 balls.
(Definitely a double batcher!)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees.
Combine green beans, asparagus, soup and melted butter in baking dish.
Stir into mixture all of the Durkee fried onions except for 1/3 cup.
Top with remaining fried onions and bake until browned.

title: creamed beef
directions: Braise ground beef; season to taste with salt and pepper. Drain grease and discard.
Melt butter in pan; add flour and milk to make a thick gravy.
Use more/less milk as needed.
Stir in braised beef.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve on toast or biscuits.
Serve with hashed brown potatoes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add pumpkin. Add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Frost with Orange Icing.

title: lunchbox cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together flour, soda, sugar, eggs, butter (softened) and fruit cocktail (undrained). Beat for 3 minutes. Pour batter into pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips, pecans (chopped) and white sugar. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed above, into a blender for 20 seconds on blend setting. Pour into greased 9 inch pie pan.

title: tangy peach-yogurt shake
directions: In blender or food processor, whirl peaches, the yogurt and allspice until smooth.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: miss opal's peach salad
directions: Combine water, sugar, crushed pineapple and heat to boiling. Add peach jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese to hot mixture and stir until melted.
Mix well.
Chill until thickened, but not jelled!
Add chopped canned peaches and Cool Whip and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill!

title: santa fe stew
directions: Brown beef and 1/2 onion.
Mix other ingredients in pot. Simmer 2 hours.
Serve with grated cheese, sour cream and/or onions.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the chopped nuts on top.

title: nut rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then divide into 12 small balls. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out chilled dough and cut into wedges.
Fill with your favorite filling (nut, apricot or poppy seed).
Roll up, beginning with wider side, as for crescent.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: lasagna(makes two casseroles!!)
directions: Meat Sauce:
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add Prego spaghetti sauce, salt, pepper, onions and oregano.
Simmer for 1/2 hour. Cheese Filling:
Mix together beaten eggs, cottage cheese (or Ricotta), Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.

title: good french dressing
directions: Put in stew pan; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Will fill a quart jar.
Will keep in refrigerator for 6 months or longer.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Pour off grease.
In small bowl, mix flour, salt, garlic, pepper and undrained mushrooms.
Stir into meat.
Cook 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Stir in soup, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream, heat through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil. Form into patties.
Heat oil in skillet. Fry patties until browned well on both sides, covered. Place patties on paper towels on plate to soak up any excess oil. Good cold too!

title: jamaican coffee
directions: Fill 6 warmed cups 3/4 full of hot coffee. Then top with Tia Maria.
Sweeten lightly with sugar to taste and serve.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: tofu croquette
directions: Cook onion in cooking oil until tender; blend in flour.
Add milk and stir while it thickens.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well and cool.
Shape into patties.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry in deep hot fat until done.
Makes 25 croquettes.

title: middle eastern pasta sauce
directions: Saute onion and pepper in olive oil and lemon juice until translucent.
Add sauce and cinnamon.
Heat and cook briefly to blend flavors.
Serve over favorite pasta.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Trim all but a thin layer of fat from chops.
Heat frying pan, then add chops.
Brown chops on both sides quickly.
Remove chops. Saute onions and bell pepper in drippings for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain off any fat.
Add brown sugar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, salt, mustard and water; mix well.
Place chops in single layer in pan.
Add tomato sauce around chops and cover pan.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes until tender.
Place chops on heated platter.
Skim fat from sauce and spoon sauce over chops.
Serves 6.

title: bob jones' egg nog
directions: Whip cream until stiff, adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Separate eggs. Whip whites very stiff, adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Whip yolks until creamy, adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Continue beating until all sugar is dissolved.
Add liquors to yolks, mixing well.
Stir in milk.
Fold in whites thoroughly and then whipped cream.

title: pizza crackers
directions: Spread one side of each cracker with pizza sauce.
Top each with a piece of cheese and a slice of pepperoni.
Arrange crackers on a paper towel lined plate.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 30 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts, rotating dish 2 or 3 times during cooking.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.

title: crab toast
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients at room temperature.
Add crabmeat. Split muffins and spread with mix.
Freeze for a few hours (not frozen).
Take out and cut into 6ths while partially frozen.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Broil until bubbly.

title: fried rice almond
directions: Cook onion, green pepper, garlic salt and pepper in oil for 5 minutes.
Add rice, soy sauce and almonds.
Mix well and cook for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: fudge cake
directions: Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gnocchi
directions: Boil potatoes and mash.
Spread on board to cool.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour slowly to make soft, pliable dough.
Cut and roll into 1-inch size pieces.
Drop gnocchi into boiling salted water.
Cover and simmer until gnocchi come to surface and are tender.
Drain well.
In serving dish, add spaghetti sauce and mix gently.
Top with grated cheese.

title: 1-2-3 peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add Bisquick.
Drop from point of spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chestnut leaves for whooping cough
directions: Let stand 10 to
15 minutes.
One or two cups a day for adults.

title: fried won ton
directions: Chop all ingredients fine.
Place in bowl and mix soy sauce, sesame oil, cornstarch and water.
Cook to thicken.
Wrap meat mixture in won ton skins. Cook in hot oil. Drain and serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: barbecued butter beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole and cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last hour.

title: easy cream cheese cake
directions: Whip together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in.
Spread crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour cream cheese mixture in.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes into small pieces.
Boil potatoes along with salt, pepper and chopped onion in just enough water to cover potatoes.
When tender, add milk and simmer until thick.
(More or less milk may be needed.)

title: kix bars
directions: Place cereal in large mixing bowl.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and margarine.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring frequently.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal; stir to coat.
Spread in 11 x 7-inch dish sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Press evenly in pan.
Cool. Makes 24 bars.

title: simple strawberry dessert cake
directions: Slice pound cake.
Place slices on plates (one or two slices per plate).
Pour some strawberries and juice over each slice.
If you choose to, add whipped cream on top.

title: pork roast with tangy sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine salt, garlic salt and 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.
Rub on roast.
Place roast, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in preheated 325° oven for 2 hours (170° for 40 minutes per pound).

title: salisbury steak
directions: In large bowl, combine 1/4 cup soup and remaining ingredients except water.
Shape into patties.
Brown in large skillet.
Drain grease.
Combine rest of soup and water.
Spoon over patties and simmer over low heat 20 minutes.

title: easy cream cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Lightly grease one large or two medium baking sheets.
Prepare Cream Cheese Filling as directed; set aside.
Stir together biscuit mix and sugar in mixing bowl. Stir in milk and butter until blended.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet to form 16 mounds.

Make a shallow well in center of each mound using the back of a spoon. Place one heaping tablespoonful of Cream Cheese Filling into each well. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes. Drizzle with Confectioners Glaze. Best served warm. Makes 16 pastries.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cup up cooked meat (any kind).
May use roast left over or, if using raw meat, pork chops or steak, brown on each side and cook a few minutes before adding to casserole.
Hamburger or sausage may be used; cook and drain grease before adding to casserole.
Saute carrot and onion in a little margarine or oil; mix all in mixing bowl.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (covered).
The last 10 minutes, uncover to brown top. Delicious!!

title: applesauce cake
directions: A Nellie Snowdeal recipe.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix all together well; set aside.
Mix walnuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Put 1/2 of batter in 9-inch tube pan (greased and floured), then 1/2 of topping (walnuts, sugar and cinnamon), then rest of batter and other half of topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake the day before serving.
Break half of cake into little pieces in a very large container (trifle bowl).
Pour 1/4 cup kahlua over cake.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle candy over Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, ending with candy.

title: pluckett cake
directions: Make mixture of first 3 ingredients.
Cut each biscuit into quarters; roll in sugar mixture and drop into Bundt pan.
Pour remaining sugar mixture over top; sprinkle with nuts.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks oleo; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Pour glaze over top of cake after you remove from pan while cake is still hot.

title: basic tomato sauce
directions: Combine everything together.
Then simmer uncovered for 2 hours.
Just before
done, add tomato paste to thicken.
Put in jars while hot and seal.

title: cappuccino
directions: Mix well.
Add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to one cup boiling water.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Divide among 4 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake for 20 to 30 minutes more.
Yields 80 to 100 servings.

title: pound cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter (don't use margarine) and sugar.
Divide cream cheese into 1/3's.
Alternately add 2 eggs and 1/3 package cream cheese times 3 until 6 eggs and 1 package cream cheese are used. Beat 3 to 4 minutes each time between additions.
Add cake flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased large tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours at most.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternately with the milk.
Add figs, pecans and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Good; nice and moist.

title: plantation chicken
directions: Boil chicken, save broth.
Chop onion, pepper and celery; saute in margarine.
Add chicken.
Add soup, milk, and 1 1/2 cups chicken broth; stir until smooth.
Take off heat, add well beaten eggs and bread crumbs.
Pour in large pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with grated cheese when done.
Serve when cheese melts.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix well and chill. Roll to 1/4-inch thick on floured board and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Cool and frost or decorate as desired.

title: peppermint candy
directions: Place candy coating in a microwave safe bowl; microwave at medium (50% power) for four minutes, stirring after two minutes. Stir in candy, and spoon mixture into a greased wax paper lined cookie sheet. Spread thin and chill until firm. Break into small pieces. Store in an airtight container. Yield three dozen. May substitute lemon candy for peppermint.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted butter.
Save 1/2 cup of this for topping and press the rest into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together 6 ounces Cool Whip and cream cheese, then spread over cookie crumbs.
Mix milk with instant pudding and spread over creamed mixture.
Take remaining Cool Whip and spread over pudding.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cookie crumbs.
Chill.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar and water; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add syrup.
Cover saucepan and cook until syrup begins to boil. Remove top and cook, without stirring, to 255°.
Remove from heat and pour in a fine stream over egg whites, beating constantly. Continue beating until mixture holds shape and loses its gloss. Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop quickly from tip of spoon onto waxed paper in individual peaks.
Makes 30 pieces.

title: peaches for fried pies
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
Put in hot pint jars and seal or it can be put in freezer.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer all ingredients.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and bake 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in an unbaked pie crust.

title: easy apple dumpling
directions: Roll biscuits thin and fill with apple filling.
(Grand biscuits use 2 tablespoons; regular size use 1 tablespoon.)
Put each dumpling in a glass dish sprayed with Pam.
In saucepan, bring to boil the sugar, cinnamon, margarine and 7-Up.
Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° until brown in color.

title: teddi's potluck chili
directions: Brown and drain the ground meat.
If using fresh kidney beans, cook about an hour and drain off all water before putting the ingredients together.
If using canned kidney beans, combine all the ingredients in a large pot together.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown beef, drain fat.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Simmer partially covered. Stir several times. Cook about 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil chicken, broth and butter.
Add onion and celery.
Cool 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Gradually add all soups, milk and chopped Velveeta cheese.
Add grated cheese.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roast walnut pieces on baking sheet for 5 to 8 minutes or until fragrant.
Place spinach in salad bowl and toss with apple wedges and lemon juice.
Add walnuts; mix well. Whisk oils and raspberry vinegar in a bowl; pour over spinach mixture.
Add sesame seed.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Toss well and serve.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine just until tender.
Add tomatoes and sauce and all seasonings.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add macaroni.
Simmer another 10 to 15 minutes.
Mixture should be fairly thick.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "my own" chile
directions: In heavy large pan, add some cooking or olive oil.
Brown meat, onion, garlic and celery until meat is done.
Add salt, pepper, cumin seed and chili powder.
Stir well.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Rinse cans and jars and add to soup.
Cook only until chile comes to a boil.
Stir well while heating.

title: yogurt orange popsicles
directions: Mix together and freeze in molds or ice cube trays.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain and add all other ingredients.
Simmer and serve.

title: herb bread
directions: Mix together and spread on French bread.
Heat in foil in a 400° oven for 15 minutes. Easy but very tasty.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Combine milk and egg in mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together and add (fold in) zucchini.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into 375° deep fat fryer.
Turn only once.
Drain on paper towel. Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen fritters.

title: very strawberry pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cubes and stir until melted.
Prepare pie filling mix with 3/4 cup milk as directed on package for pie; let stand about 2 minutes.
Blend in gelatin.
Chill, if necessary, until thickened.
Fold in 2 cups of the whipped topping and strawberries.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and additional strawberries, if desired.

title: peach salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
May be refrigerated up to 2 days.
Makes about 3 cups.
Good with grilled beef, chicken, pork, or fish.

title: strawberry banana milkshakes
directions: Ingredients are per shake.

title: ukranian bread
directions: In a small bowl dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
In a large bowl beat eggs and yolks until lemon colored, gradually adding sugar.
Add margarine, salt, lemon juice and peel.
Beat well.
Blend into yeast mixture.
Add 6 cups flour and beat until smooth.
By hand, stir in enough flour to make dough soft.
Turn onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic. Sprinkle with raisins and knead for 5 more minutes.
Place in a greased bowl turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Punch down.
Turn onto a lightly floured board and divide into thirds.
Let rise for 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise in a warm place to double.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and parboil.
Cool.
Remove each leaf.
Line roasting pan with some of the cabbage leaves.
Take half of the sauerkraut and spread on top of cabbage.
Mix hamburg, pork and rice together.
Add salt and pepper as wanted.
Take each cabbage leaf and stuff with the meat mixture (amount according to size of leaf).
When all meat mix is used up, add the rest of the sauerkraut on.
Roll up leaves.
Pour 1/2 cup warm water over all. Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water as needed.
Serve with carrots.

title: escalloped carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Cook onions in butter 2-3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, mustard and milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt. In 2 quart casserole arrange layers of carrots and cheese slices. Pour in mustard mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and bake 30-40 minutes.

title: broccoli ham roll-ups
directions: Bring broccoli to boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Leave whole; drain water.
Wrap slices of ham around broccoli and put in buttered casserole.
Pour soup over all.
Add onion flakes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crumbly apple pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon; pour into prepared pie crust. Mix and sprinkle on top the brown sugar, flour, butter and salt. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer all the ingredients exactly in the order in which they are given.
This is a very attractive dish when prepared on a large serving platter and served with fresh tortilla chips.

title: peanut sesame noodles
directions: Cook spaghetti until al dente.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water and toss with 2 tablespoons sesame oil.
Set aside.
Place remaining sesame oil in large heated frying pan.
Add green onions, garlic and pepper flakes.
Stir over medium heat until onions have softened, 2 minutes.
Add spaghetti, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce.
Heat mixture, tossing to combine for 3 or 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and cilantro.
Add salt to taste. Transfer to serving bowl.
Makes 4 servings.

title: choco-cherry nut drops
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Then cream butter and gradually add brown sugar and white sugar; cream well. Blend in egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add the dry ingredients gradually and mix well.
Stir in morsels, nuts and cherries.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Yield:
5 to 6 dozen.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Fry meat in butter; drain.
Add all ingredients, except noodles (shells).
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Cook noodles and add to pot.

title: chicken-rice skillet
directions: In skillet or electric frypan, stir together oil, soy sauce, onion and garlic.
Add chicken and brown over medium heat.
Season with ginger and pepper.
Push chicken to center with pieces overlapping.
Pour 2 1/4 cups water around chicken and add bouillon and rice.
Cover and simmer about 35 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water, if needed.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
May frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: gilbert's garden pasta sauce
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions and garlic in hot oil 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter 2 cookie sheets, 15 1/2 x 12-inches and keep warm.
Mix baking soda, 1 teaspoon water and vanilla.
Mix sugar, 1 cup water and the corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to 240° on candy thermometer or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball that flattens when removed from water.
Stir in margarine and peanuts.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 300° or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water separates into hard, brittle threads.
Watch carefully so mixture does not burn. Immediately remove from heat.
Quickly stir in baking soda mixture until light and foamy.
Pour half of the candy mixture onto each cookie sheet and quickly spread about 1/4-inch thick.
Cool. Break into pieces.

title: peanut butter sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs and oil. Add remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Press with fork and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: o' henry candy
directions: Mix sugar and white syrup to rolling boil (do not overcook). Add peanut butter; blend until smooth.
Add Special K; blend until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with melted chocolate.

title: nacho hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spread bottom of pie plate with cream cheese.
Add beans, spreading evenly over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with olives.
Spread salsa over mixture and top with Cheddar cheese.
Heat at 375° until Cheddar cheese has melted.
Serve warm with taco chips.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice rolls in halves.
Melt oleo; add mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire; stir well.
