Add ham and cheese; mix well.
Spread over bottom half of roll until covered.
Place top half of rolls over mixture.
Replace in tin and wrap with foil. Place overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake yellow pudding cake mix in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is cooking, bring to a boil pineapple and sugar; boil 5 minutes.
When cake is done, pour pineapple over cake; let cool. When ready to serve, mix pudding.
Spread over cake.
Spread coconut over pudding.
Cut bananas over coconut.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and add cherries.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; beat in oil and sugar, then add zucchini and vanilla.
In another bowl, add dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt).
Add dry ingredients to other bowl. Mix all together.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let it sit in pan for 10 minutes to cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter. Mix until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix until smooth.
Put into crusts.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Take 1 cup warm water, dry yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar; mix well.
Let rise.
Now, take 2 cups water, 1 cup sugar, shortening and salt; heat together until shortening melts.
Let cool.
Add about 7 cups or more flour, 2 eggs and the first yeast mixture together.
Beat with beater like making a cake.
Set aside to rise at room temperature.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and roll out rolls in shape you want.
These rolls can be precooked and frozen.

title: banana marlow
directions: Melt marshmallows in boiling water.
Add the banana pulp and lemon juice.
Cool.
When quite cool and slightly thickened, combine with the cream, which has been whipped.
Pour into trays and freeze without stirring.
Serves 6.

title: confetti salad
directions: Cook shells according to package; drain.
Rinse until cool and drain well.
Combine Italian dressing, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
In a large bowl, blend well.
Add all ingredients to dressing mixture.
Toss lightly until evenly coated.
Chill.

title: shontel's easy dump cake
directions: Pour fruit into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan (drain 1/2 of liquid).

title: easy oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters and artichokes; save juice.
Saute onions in butter.
Chop oysters and artichokes.
Add soup and juice to desired consistency.

title: chile verde
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add jalapenos, onions and tomatoes; boil for 20 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend to desired consistency.
Over medium-high heat, return to a boil.
It is then you're ready to put on top of your food.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Dip cutlets in mixture of beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Pat coating of crumbs over meat surface.
Heat oil in large skillet; brown veal on both sides.
Place meat in large baking dish. Combine and heat remaining ingredients except cheeses for 10 minutes.
Pour over veal, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cover tightly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover, place slice of Mozzarella cheese over each cutlet and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: graham cracker crust(no bake)
directions: Blend together and press in pie plate.
Chill before filling.

title: louisiana chicken and rice
directions: Place all ingredients except chicken in casserole.
Mix well. Place chicken onto and push into liquid so it is covered.
Cover dish and microwave on High 24 to 27 minutes. Rotate dish several times.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: pineapple-lime velvet salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve lemon and lime gelatins in boiling water.
Add cheese and beat with an electric mixer until smooth. Chill mixture to consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in celery, pecans and pineapple.
Fold whipped topping thoroughly into jello mixture.
Turn into 2 shallow 2-quart baking dishes. Cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
You can use a 13 ounce can chilled, whipped evaporated milk instead of topping. Makes 24 servings.

title: butter sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until fluffy; add scalded milk and vanilla, beating constantly.
Add flour and baking powder. Fold in melted butter or margarine.
Batter will be very thin. Pour into 3 (9-inch) well-greased
layer
pans.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice cake with your favorite frosting.

title: toasted meringue cake
directions: Cream shortening, add 2 cups brown sugar and mix well.
Add 2 egg whites and 4 yolks.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk

title: peppy cheese dip
directions: Blend ingredients (I use my food processor).
Chill and serve with raw vegetables.

title: quick flavor with instant coffee
directions: Dissolve coffee granules or powder in equal amount of water. Shake with coconut.
Sprinkle on cupcakes or ice cream.

title: amish pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients, then add water, stirring just until mixed.
Add dry ingredients to the pumpkin mixture.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9x5 loaf pans.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large bowl.
Add next 9 ingredients; mix well. Chill until nearly firm. Shape into ball. Roll in pecans and parsley flakes.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice to serve.

title: white chili
directions: Sprinkle Southwest seasoning on chicken breasts and cook in microwave until done.
Don't overcook the chicken but make sure it is done (no pink in the middle).
While chicken breasts are cooking, combine above ingredients in pan and cook on medium.
Add cooked chicken breasts and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir to ensure it doesn't stick to bottom of pan.
Garnish with sour cream and shredded Monterey Jack cheese.

title: french vanilla icing
directions: Cook
milk
and
flour until thick (similar to starting gravy).
Cool
completely in fridge.
Beat butter, shortening, sugar and
vanilla
until
creamy.
Add cooked milk and flour. Beat 10 minutes.
Should resemble the inside of a Twinkie.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to boil.
Stir constantly until sugar is fully dissolved.
Remove from heat, beat in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour in buttered pan to cool and set.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon coated pecans
directions: Boil until mixture spins a thread. Pour in 3 cups of pecans. Stir quickly until pecans are coated and just about to get hard. Pour out on tin foil.
Separate with a fork.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in pieces; fry until medium done.
Put beans in oven dish; add bacon, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard and sugar.
Stir well; slice onion and separate.
Layer on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: crispy chicken rolls
directions: Bone chicken breasts if not previously boned.
Pound each half breast to about 1/4 inch thickness.
Combine chopped shrimp, margarine and green onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon shrimp mixture onto center of each breast.
Roll breast and skewer or secure with toothpick.
Heat 1 inch oil in skillet.
Make batter from flour, baking powder, salt and water.
Roll or dip each breast in batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown (about 15 minutes), turning frequently.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve quickly to retain crispiness.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat water, brown sugar, shortening and salt to 115° to 120°, stirring constantly.
Add flour mixture; beat at low speed for 30 seconds, then on high for 3 minutes.
Knead in whole wheat flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to coat.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size.
Punch down; divide in half and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and place in greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Cover; let rise until nearly double.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes.

title: marie moncrief's coconut-black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, coconut and extract.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 65 minutes or until cake tests done.
Pour the following hot syrup over hot cake in pan.

title: orange blossom muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine orange juice, 1/4 cup sugar, oil and egg.
Add biscuit mix and beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Stir in marmalade and pecans.
Grease muffin pan or line with paper cups.
Fill each cup 2/3 full with batter.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in bowl.
Bring to boil water,
butter and cooking oil in saucepan.
Then pour in bowl with dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Then add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled corn
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Fill jars 3/4 full of corn.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Pour enough boiling water to completely cover contents in the jar and seal.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Combine
tomatoes
and onions;	add 3 tablespoons salt. Add enough cold water
to
cover.
In
separate
container add 1 1/2 tablespoons salt and
enough
cold	water
to
cover the peppers. Let each pan
set
10 to 12 hours.	Drain vegetables and rinse well.
Combine green tomatoes, onions and peppers in large pot and add enough	water to cover.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes (onions should
be	clear,	but not mushy).
Drain; set aside to cool.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Bring soup to boil.
Add cream cheese.
Cook until melted. Add gelatin and cool in refrigerator.
Add other ingredients and pour into lightly oiled pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Can double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: To make crust, mix first three ingredients; press in 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.

title: peanut butter balls(no bake)
directions: Cream together peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: pastel de elote
directions: Sift
flour, measure and sift with corn meal and baking powder and
salt
into mixing bowl.
Cream butter and sugar in another bowl
and add eggs one at a time, mixing in well.
Add chilies, corn
and
cheese;	mix well.
Blend creamed mixture into flour mixture.
Pour into greased and floured baking dish (8 x
x 2-inch) and put into preheated oven (350°).
Bake for 5
minutes at	350°
and
reduce
to 300° and bake for 55 minutes.
Time of preparation: 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple steak
directions: Mix ingredients and marinate steak 2 hours or more.
Place steak and pineapple on skewers.
Barbecue or broil shish kabobs until preferred doneness.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, soda, raisins, nuts and flour.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.

title: michael's lentil "stoup"
directions: Pressure cook lentils 10 to 15 minutes (1 hour regular cooking).
Saute vegies in a bit of oil.
Mix lentils, vegies, garlic and spices.
Add water to desired thickness.
Serve warm. Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: funny bunny cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line large cookie sheet (17 x 14-inch) with foil.
Divide cookie dough in half; refrigerate remaining dough.
Divide remaining dough in half; shape one-half into large ball.
To form bunny's body, press ball into 6-inch circle 1-inch from bottom of foil-lined cookie sheet.
Divide remaining dough in half; shape into ball and press into 4-inch circle so it just touches other circle.
To form ears, divide remaining dough in half.
Shape into ears 5-inches long and 2-inches apart just touching head.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 12 minutes or until set. Cool completely.
Remove from foil.
Spread bunny with frosting. Decorate as desired.
Makes 2 cookies.
(M&M's make cute bunny.)

title: christmas coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, measure butter, cream cheese and sugar and beat together. Add egg, almond extract and orange juice; beat well. Mix together flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture until well blended. Stir in 4 cups of coconut; cover and chill 1 hour.

title: homemade soup
directions: Fill a large pot halfway with water.
Put in the onion and bring to a boil.
Add the cut up potatoes.
Boil until they are soft.
Add all vegetables, tomato sauce and hamburger meat.
Let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: diabetic orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and run slightly.

title: impossible chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw. Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onions in pie plate.
Beat eggs and Bisquick mix in blender until smooth, 15 seconds or 1 minute by hand.
Pour into plate over other ingredients.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes. Put remaining cheese on top.
Cook only until cheese is melted. Cool 5 minutes to set.

title: chicken baked
directions: Mix and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325°.

title: hamburg tomato rice soup
directions: In lg stew pot combine veggies, bouillon, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to boil then let simmer.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar;
add
fruit
and egg, then milk and flour sifted with baking
powder and salt.	Bake in muffin tins at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, 1/3 cup pancake mix, lemon peel and rhubarb. Toss together.
Place in 9-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining dry ingredients; stir in eggs until coarse.
Sprinkle over rhubarb. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased dish until brown in a 375° oven.

title: shrimp and sausage dinner
directions: Place in a large pot of water on stove.
Add crab and shrimp boil.
Bring to a boil; add sausage and let boil 5 minutes.
Add corn and boil, 7 to 10 minutes longer.
Add shrimp and cook, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange all ingredients on a large platter and serve with melted butter and cocktail sauce.
Serves 6 to 8. (Great with a green salad and garlic bread.)

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle top with additional cracker crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: end of the garden relish
directions: Cook beans and carrots separately until tender.
Soak the rest of the vegetables overnight in salt and water.
Drain and add the cooked carrots and green beans.
Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Add all vegetables to this mixture and boil together for 10 minutes, then spoon into jars.
Makes about 7 half-pint jars.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup milk.
Pat half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: no rise yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt stick of butter and add to yeast and water.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Stir well.
Add flour.
Mix all together and pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Flatten biscuits individually on cookie sheet. spoon pizza sauce on biscuit. Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.
You may add other toppings such as sausage, pepperoni, mushrooms, etc.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add all other ingredients and blend. Fold into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: cucumber salad
directions: This recipe may be made as large or as small as you want. Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: "in-law" chicken pie
directions: Cut up chicken; cover with water.
Add the salt and poultry seasoning to the water.
Cover the pan and cook until chicken is done.
Cool.
Remove chicken from the bone and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove about 3 cups broth from cooking pot and place in another cooker.
Make a thickening, using about 3 tablespoons of flour and 1/2 cup water.
Stir together until smooth.
Pour this thickening into hot broth and stir together until gravy is thick and bubbly.
Pour this gravy over chicken in pan.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg; add melted butter and about 1 1/2 cups milk together.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Make a batter that is stiffer than pancakes, but not as stiff as drop dumplings. Drop by big mixing spoonfuls on gravy.
Bake at 375° until brown and cooked through.
Spoon biscuit on plate and top with chicken and gravy.

title: old fashioned new york style cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Let cheese reach room temperature. Melt butter; mix butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and graham crackers together.
Put in bottom of 9-inch spring pan, place in freezer until mixture is completed.
In a separate bowl mix together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until reaches a smooth texture.
Mix in eggs, vanilla, cornstarch and sour cream.
When smooth, pour mixture into spring pan.
You may bake now either in water or just in spring pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, turn oven down to 250°, bake additional 45 minutes.
Shut oven off, let cake sit 3 hours inside.
Place in fridge at least 8 hours prior to serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix
first
ingredients and set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar;
add
eggs, mixing well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add
buttermilk and flour alternately to Crisco and sugar
mixture
in	thirds.
Mix
well.
Add red food coloring mixture; mix well.	Add vinegar last.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: snowy white fudge
directions: Let butter begin to melt in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Brush sides of pan with melted butter.
Add evaporated milk and sugar. Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, about 8 minutes, whisking constantly to dissolve sugar.
Cook over medium-high heat, whisking frequently to soft ball stage, 236°, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add candy wafers, marshmallow cream, walnuts and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Pour into well buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: penuche frosting
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan and stir in brown sugar. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir over low heat 2 minutes.
Stir in milk and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar. Place the pan in a bowl of ice water.
Beat the frosting until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Boil the cauliflower and then batter it in eggs and flour. Deep fry in vegetable oil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove 12 large leaves from cabbage.
Trim off thick part of each leaf.
Let boiling water stand on leaves a few minutes, so they become easy to roll.
Combine meat, rice, grated onion, eggs, salt, pepper.
Place mounds of meat mixture in cup part of each leaf.
Loosely fold over sides of each leaf; roll up.
Start heating oven to 375°.
In bottom of Dutch oven, place a few of remaining cabbage leaves.
Arrange layers of stuffed cabbage with seam sides down, and sliced onion in Dutch oven.
Pour on tomato sauce, tomatoes, lemon juice.
Add 1 tsp. salt, 1/4 tsp. pepper. Bring to boil on top of range.
Sprinkle with sugar to taste. Bake, covered, 1 hour; uncover; bake 2 hours.
(Serves 8.)

title: hot spice sauce for plum pudding or fruitcake(for 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot on warmed pudding or cake.

title: fake raspberry jam
directions: Cook ground tomatoes and sugar together for 15 minutes.
Add the package of gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Put in jars and seal.
Invert jars after 1 hour to distribute the fruit.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Mix crushed pineapple and marshmallows together and put into a bowl with a cover.
Let set overnight (approximately 8 hours) in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour sauce(for corn salad)
directions: Mix together; cook
until
thick.
(If desired, you can add more vinegar.) Let cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples, water, cinnamon and nutmeg and salt in bottom of sugar baking dish.
Bake topping of sugar, flour and oleo.
Mix together and press over apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: vanilla almond coffee
directions: Add the two extracts together and shake thoroughly.
Brew your coffee and add extract mixture to taste.
Adds a wonderful flavor, especially for decaffeinated brews.

title: pea and tomato soup
directions: A novel and excellent combination is a mixture of a can of cream of pea soup and a can of cream of tomato soup.

title: banana bread
directions: Melt and cool butter.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat and whip 1 1/2 minutes. Add bananas, sour cream and nuts to flour mixture.
Blend 1/2 minute.
Bake in a loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add onions and mushrooms; cook and stir until onions are tender.
Remove vegetables and drain.
Brown meat in same skillet, adding shortening if necessary.
Remove pan from heat.
Sprinkle salt, marjoram, thyme and pepper over meat.
Mix flour and broth; stir into skillet. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; boil and stir one minute. Stir in wine.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Liquid should always just cover meat.
If necessary, add more wine and broth, one part broth to two parts wine.
Gently stir in onions and mushrooms.
Cook, uncovered, 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: creamy mandarin salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Set aside to cool. Blend all ingredients and chill at least two hours.
Serve on spinach or romaine lettuce.
Top with chow mein noodles.

title: dee's bowtie pasta
directions: In bowl, combine pasta and vegetables.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over pasta.
Let stand 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: seafood vera cruz
directions: Place fish fillets in Pyrex dish; salt and pepper to taste. Add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; allow to marinate while preparing vegetables.
Saute onion in olive oil until golden.
Add tomatoes, pepper, garlic, capers, black olives, tomato paste and chopped parsley.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes.
Top fish with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes per inch of thickness of fish.

title: artichoke heart salad
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl with mixer, beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and molasses until blended.
Beat in 1 cup of flour, salt, baking soda and spices until well mixed.
With spoon, stir in enough of remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Lightly grease bottom of flat bottomed 3-inch glass.
Dip into small bowl of sugar.
Use glass to flatten balls to 3-inch diameter, dipping each time in sugar. Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in two 9-inch round pans. Let cakes partially cool and poke holes in the top.
Pour over each cake 1/2 cup of Kahlua.
Let the cakes cool completely.
Cut cakes into small pieces.
Make chocolate mousse as per package directions.
Using a large punch bowl, pat cake pieces on the bottom of bowl.
Place part of the chocolate mousse on top of the cake pieces, then layer with Cool Whip and crushed Skor bars. Keep layering until punch bowl is filled.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed Skor bars.
Dig in!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together first five ingredients on low speed.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Alternately add chopped nuts and fold in stiff beaten egg whites.
Bake until done in a tube pan at 300°, about 2 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until creamy.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13 pan. Cool. Punch holes in cake where juice can get in layer. Pour strawberries over cake. Put Cool Whip on top. Cool before serving.

title: hearty oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Combine pancake mix, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans; pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before frosting.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: gram's fresh peach pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and peaches.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add lemon juice and cool.
Meanwhile make crumbs with flour, 1 cup sugar and margarine.
Combine and mix until crumbs are fine.
Put peach mixture in pastry shell.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 20 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese bacon bars
directions: Blend all ingredients well; spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes and cut into small squares.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and crumble. Add onion and saute.
Drain bacon grease.
Add vinegar, garlic powder, catsup and brown sugar to bacon mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and add beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or heat in crock pot.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with 1 crust; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour filling in pie pan.
Top with second crust.
Seal and crimp edges.
Slit top of crust to vent and bake at 375° for 45-50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: golden baked fish
directions: Place fish in pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Spread on fish.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork and is lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Mix butter and peanut butter; add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan and line with a strip of wax paper.
Grease the paper.
Place the flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
While beating, add the beer slowly.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into loaf pan and top with the melted butter. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Remove chicken; reserve 1/2 cup of chicken stock.
Cut chicken into large bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.
Combine soups, tomatoes, chicken stock, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
In a 3-quart casserole, make 3 layers in the following order:
torn tortillas, chicken, tomato mixture, chopped onions and grated cheese.
Use all ingredients being sure cheese is on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: aunt eleanore dish
directions: In a large frying pan, crumble and fry sausage and ground meat together until good and brown.
Drain meat in a colander and return to large frying pan.
Add sauerkraut and 1 can water; bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 12 minutes or less.
Test noodles for doneness after 8 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix onion, pepper and 1 package dried beef; mix with cream cheese. Form a ball and roll into rest of the dried beef. Enjoy. Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: easy layered salad
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer lettuce, green pepper, onions and peas.
Do not toss.
Spread salad dressing over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken chili
directions: Heat half the olive oil in a Dutch oven over high heat.
Add the onion and garlic; saute for 5 minutes.
Add the red and jalapeno peppers and saute over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in the chili powder, cumin, coriander and cinnamon; cook for 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Brown the chicken in batches in the remaining 3 tablespoons oil in a large skillet just until cooked through.
Add the chicken, tomatoes with the puree, olives and beer to the Dutch oven and stir to combine. Simmer over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Stir in the chocolate and season to taste with salt.
Serve immediately.
Pass the sour cream, Cheddar cheese, scallions and avocado in separate small bowls.
Makes 6 portions.

title: cream cheese crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on toast or bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: angel food candy
directions: Cut chocolate into small pieces.
Set aside. Cut wax into small pieces. Set aside.
In heavy 4-quart Dutch oven, combine corn syrup and brown sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 300° on candy thermometer, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Carefully stir in baking soda (mixture will foam up).
Pour at once into a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
When cool, turn out of pan.
Break into pieces using wooden spoon.
In a
double boiler, combine chocolate chips, chocolate pieces, butter and wax.
Stir mixture until melted and smooth. Remove from heat, leaving in double boiler. Dip candy into chocolate using large cooking fork.
Place on waxed paper lined baking sheets.
Let stand until chocolate is set. Store in cool place.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter and graham cracker crumbs; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: parmesan potatoes(microwave recipe)
directions: Place butter in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf dish.
Microwave on High 1/2 to 1 minute to melt.
Stir potatoes into melted butter to coat.
Add cheese to taste and salt.
Stir well.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back one corner to vent.
Cook on High for 15 minutes, rotating after 8 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Combine beef, beans, oregano, cumin and garlic.
Place four of the uncooked noodles in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half of the beef over noodles.
Top with 4 more noodles and the remaining noodles.

title: lobster cakes with corn chowder
directions: Mix together first 10 ingredients.
Fold in lobster meat and season to taste.
Add enough cracker crumbs until all blends together.
Form 8 small cakes.
Preheat oven to 357 degrees.
Place cakes on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
To serve, place lobster cake in soup plate.
Pour chowder around. Enjoy!

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add Milnot and water. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until desired thickness. Add 1 tablespoon butter or oleo and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Delicious served hot over hot biscuits.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Scrub and peel off potatoes.
Dice into bite-size pieces with skin on.
Mix oil and onion mix together.
In lined baking pan, place potatoes; pour oil and onion mix mixture over potatoes. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate yummy cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and blend.
Add vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 14-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy stir-fry shrimp(friday's dinner menu)
directions: Serve with green salad/low-fat Ranch dressing and crispy bread sticks

title: maple baked beans
directions: Place beans in an ovenproof crock with a lid.
Stir in all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Add apples, celery, walnuts and raisins.
Toss well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: genesis pie
directions: Fold Cool Whip into yogurt and pour into crust.
Freeze for 3 to 4 hours.
Take out of freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Beat egg yolks; add flour, mixing well.
Stir in nutmeg, mayonnaise, margarine, salt and pepper and cheese.
Add broccoli, mixing lightly.
Beat egg whites (room temperature) until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold into broccoli mixture.
Pour into lightly buttered 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 or 40 minutes or until browned and set.

title: nanaimo bars(pronounced na-nigh-mo)
directions: In a double boiler, melt together butter or margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Add egg and vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir in graham crumbs, coconut and walnuts. Press mixture firmly into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: mors kake
directions: Beat eggs and powdered sugar well.
Add almonds, walnuts, lemon extract, warm milk and flour which baking powder has been added to.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for 45 minutes.
Decorate cake with whipped cream and fruit.

title: punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
This is the base of the punch. Freeze base in 4 equal parts in containers.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a 2-quart souffle dish.
Wash each vegetable and slice very thin.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes on the bottom of the dish and dot with butter.
Repeat the process with the other vegetables in order; dot with butter in between each layer.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon strips. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soften cracker crumbs with milk and let set 10 minutes.
Add egg to all of this which has not been mixed together.
Add a can of tomato paste or catsup on top.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: triple-treat brownie crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Chop unsweetened chocolate.
Combine 6 tablespoons of the butter and half of the chopped chocolate in a saucepan over the lowest heat.
Let melt and stir until smooth. Remove from heat and let cool completely.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Mix applesauce, brown sugar and melted shortening.
Sift in flour mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Put in a greased pan (7 x 11-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: basic butter cookie dough
directions: In a large bowl with electric mixer beat butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and salt until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour; beat until well mixed.
Cover dough.
Chill 1 hour or place in freezer 30 minutes.
Work with 1/4 dough at a time (keep remaining dough chilled).
Roll out 1/4-inch thick between sheets of wax paper.
Cut or mold dough into desired shapes.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place cookies on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until cookies are lightly browned.
Remove to rack.
Cool completely.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: bible cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Follow Solomon's advice (2 Samuel 22:43, first choice, beat).
Mix well, then pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pie crust(for 9-inch double crust pie)
directions: Mix together.
Roll half of dough out and place over bottom and sides of pie plate.
Fill as desired.
Top with remaining dough. Flute edges and slit top.
Bake until lightly golden or as directed according to desired pie.

title: electric mixer rolls
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add sugar. Dissolve yeast in milk and let stand 5 minutes.
Add 3 cups of flour and beat vigorously. Add salt and eggs and beat well again.
Add melted shortening or oil.
When well blended, gradually add remaining flour.
When stiff, turn onto floured board and knead.
Return to oiled bowl to rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
When light, knead before shaping into desired types of rolls.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: old time popcorn balls
directions: Butter sides of pan.
Combine sugar, water, salt, syrup and vinegar.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Stir in vanilla slowly; pour over popped corn and mix well.
Butter hands; shape into balls. Makes 20 balls.

title: punch
directions: Mix juices well with syrup before adding ginger ale.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Run through food chopper and add 2 cups sugar.
Chill.
Mix 1 cup boiling water to 1 small package raspberry jello.
Chill until partly set.
Add cranberry mixture and nuts, if desired. Chill overnight.

title: peach and pineapple conserve
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook ten minutes.
Add cherries and bring to a boil.
Bottle.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Line large baking dish with layer of tortillas.
Sprinkle with chicken broth.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add soups and chili powder.
Pour layer of soup mixture over tortillas, then layer of chicken, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour can of Ro-Tel on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to cranberries and apples.
Mix well and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Add Dream Whip and marshmallows; keep in refrigerator.

title: hoss' fat-free muffins(not the restaurant)
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased muffin pan. Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crushed oreo cookies.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar with above mix.
Mix pudding with milk and cool whip.
Layer in a flowerpot; add flowers or gummi worms if desired.

title: oven-candied sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter; stir in corn, syrup, water, brown sugar and salt. Cut potatoes in halves lengthwise.
Dip in corn syrup mixture, coating all sides.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour remaining syrup over top.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until tender and glazed, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix, then drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: macaroni hamburg casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden.
Add hamburger; cook slowly until done.
Drain excess fat.
Grease a casserole dish. Combine macaroni with all ingredients, including half of the cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Turn into casserole dish; sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Hold a few orange sections aside.
Dissolve jello in water. Stir in sherbet until dissolved.
Pour into mold or serving dish. Refrigerate until almost jelled.
Stir in oranges and whipped cream, gently.
Top with a dot of cream and an orange section. Very light and refreshing.

title: string pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and pepper until brown. Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce in separate bowl.
Combine spaghetti, Parmesan cheese, eggs and butter.
Place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread cottage cheese over the top.
Pour sauce mixture over the cottage cheese. Sprinkle with Mozzarella over this. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: frogmore stew
directions: You will also need a 6 to 8-quart stock pot and 1 large spoon with holes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar together; add the egg and beat until fluffy. Stir in the dry ingredients, buttermilk and vanilla. Add diced rhubarb and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the white sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over the batter. Drizzle the melted margarine over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine spinach, stuffing and sour cream. Spread cream mixture on squares of ham and roll, placing seam-side down in oblong baking dish. Combine milk, cornstarch and butter. Cook until thick. Stir in the Swiss cheese. Pour sauce over ham rolls and sprinkle a little additional Swiss cheese and paprika on top. Bake, covered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender; process until smooth. Makes 1 1/4 cups or 1 can.

title: frozen angel food delight
directions: Cut cake into 3 layers.
Spread lime sherbet on bottom layer. Spread second layer with lemon sherbet.
Add third cake layer. Frost with whipping cream.
Freeze.
Remove 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Any sherbet flavors may be used.
Yields 12 servings.

title: walnut and port cheese
directions: Blend together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Using a table knife, swirl Port through cheese, making streaks, but not blending in completely.
Form into a ball.
Wrap and chill at least 4 hours.
Before serving, press walnuts firmly into top and sides of cheese.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: peanut butter crunch bars
directions: Melt chips together.
Bring to a boil the Karo syrup and sugar, but do not boil.
Stir in peanut butter. Add Special K. Put in greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Pat down evenly.
Pour melted chips over and cool. Cut into bars.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar; mix in butter thoroughly.
Press mixture evenly in bottom of ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool!

title: barbecue lover's chicken
directions: In bowl combine all ingredients.
In skillet, slowly brown chicken in butter (about 25 minutes).
Add sauce mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve with rice.

title: cake icing
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add all other ingredients.

title: california-style bloody mary mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add vinegar and let cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except nuts.
Add nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add to dry jello mix.
Blend in water.
Add pineapple.
Mix well and set in refrigerator until jello sets a little.
Fold in Dream Whip and apricots; add nuts.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp wraps
directions: You also need toothpicks.

title: swedish cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, bread crumbs, eggs and water together.
Shape into meatballs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Saute onion in oil until lightly brown.
Add meatballs, chili sauce and jelly.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: strombolis
directions: In frying pan, brown ground beef; drain. Add onion and oregano, also ketchup and tomato soup.
Mix well.
Heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, add 1 stick softened butter or margarine, paprika and garlic powder; mix well. Cut the rolls. Put this mixture on rolls like a spread.
Add ground beef and top with 1 slice Mozzarella per roll. Wrap each one in Reynolds Wrap and put in oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 1 dozen Strombolis.

title: eggplant
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Stir in tomatoes and Italian dressing; simmer.
Slice eggplant 1/4-inch thick.
Combine water and egg.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Put tomato sauce over eggplant and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mom's icing
directions: Mix together and spread over cooled cake.

title: fifteen minute cake
directions: Grease a microwavable tube pan and coat with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar; pour in batter.
Put in microwave oven and cook for 10 minutes on Low power and 5 minutes on High power. Test with broom straw.
May take longer in ovens less than 600 watts.
Cool and sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook, stirring, 3 minutes or until chicken is white. Remove chicken.
Add broccoli, red pepper and chicken broth. Cover and cook until broccoli is tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add bow ties and cheese; toss until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken, broccoli and ziti
directions: Saute chicken in garlic and oil.
In large pot, boil broccoli and ziti together until done.
Add wine or broth and butter to chicken and simmer, keep stirring until ready to add to ziti and broccoli.
Simmer briefly.
Add cheese to suit your taste.

title: tofu spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Defrost spinach and drain.
Place tofu, sugar, garlic powder, lemon juice and 1 teaspoon salt.
Blend until smooth.
Taste, add more salt, if necessary.
Cover bottom of pan with sauce.
Layer noodles, 1/2 tofu filling and 1/2 spinach.
Repeat layering, ending with noodles.
Cover with sauce.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour and sugar.
Add milk and egg yolks that have been beaten.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly; pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites and bake in slow oven at 250° to 300° until brown.

title: tomato corn relish
directions: Put all ingredients in pot.
Bring corn mixture to boil; boil for 15 minutes.
Fill jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars; screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 15 minutes.
Makes several pints.

title: candied yams
directions: Put all the ingredients in a heavy pot.
Start cooking on medium heat.
After boiling point, turn to low and cook until done.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; skin, cool and dice.
Add Velveeta, mayonnaise, onion and salt to taste.
Put in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with bacon. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: 7-minute icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler. Place over boiling water.
Beat with electric mixer until thick and smooth. Spread on cake.

title: sauteed bananas
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large pan or skillet.
Add bananas and cook 2 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle with orange juice; heat and serve immediately.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add flavorings and egg yolks.
Blend well.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Quickly roll dough into long cylinder, 1-inch in diameter, and cut into 1/2-inch lengths.
Form balls from cut pieces; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a quarter cherry into center of each.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes to a golden brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Prepare Jiffy mix according to directions.
Add creamed corn. Place half of mix in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Add salsa to ground chuck; simmer 10 minutes.
Spread ground chuck over top of cornbread mix.
Sprinkle cheese over chuck mixture.
Spread remaining cornbread mix.
(Will look thin, but rises.)
Bake at 350° for exactly 50 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off apricots and pineapple.
Take 3/4 cup juice; add the sugar to it.
Boil until syrupy.
Cool.
Combine all fruit in a bowl.
Pour cooled syrup over it and stir.
Put in cupcake papers and freeze.
Take out 1/2 hour before eating.
These keep well in freezer for quite some time.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning in bowl. Mix until well blended and smooth. Pour into shallow dish. Cover top with lettuce, sprinkle with cheese then chopped tomato. Chill.
Serve with doritos.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Boil until thick.
Put cooked noodles in a 4-cup Pyrex dish. Crumble drained tuna (two 5 ounce cans) over noodles.
Pour the gravy over the tuna.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and slice medium-thick.
Combine with onions, dill and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cut up eggs.

title: sweet onion quiche
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Place crackers in casserole. Layer onions on crackers.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper, milk and Accent.
Pour over onions and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with towel for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chicken noodle tortilla soup
directions: Cook chicken in oil with onions and chili powder.
In saucepan, add and bring to a boil the water and tomatoes.
To this, stir in and boil 10 minutes or until noodles are done the Lipton noodles, chiles and garlic powder.
Then add corn and cooked chicken mixture.
Put in individual bowls and add tortilla chips, crumbled, and shredded cheese.

title: turkey au gratin
directions: Cook turkey for 3 1/2 to 4 hours at 350°.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Slice thin.
Steam broccoli 4 minutes.
Melt butter in a large pot over very low heat.
Add flour to melted butter; blend. Cook mixture for 10 minutes, stirring often to prevent burning. Add half and half, milk, cheese and garlic to flour mixture; stir until well blended.
Allow to cook until mixture thickens (10 to 15 minutes), stirring often.
Add water if necessary (a thick cheese sauce is desired).
Arrange broccoli spears in a large roasting pan.
Drape turkey slices over broccoli.
Pour cheese sauce over turkey and broccoli until all is covered.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing, macaroni, tuna, celery, green pepper, onions and pimento.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate. Serve on lettuce-lined plates.

title: poached apple halves
directions: In a shallow stainless steel pan, make a thin syrup with sugar, water and a few pieces cinnamon stick.
(Thin syrup is 1 cup sugar and 3 cups water.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add
oil,	sugar
and
zucchini; mix well. Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased
and floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake in 350° oven
for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool on rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: mama's sweet potato pudding
directions: In Georgia, I add pecans.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and stir until blended. Form into balls. Yields about 2 lbs.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Batter will be thin.
Make large thin pancakes, keeping pan well buttered.
Pancakes may be filled with preserves, ice cream, ground walnuts and powdered sugar or cooked apples.

title: surprise cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half to make two layers.
Spread strawberry jelly on top of first half and cover with other half. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until creamy.
Slowly add sugar, then flour, baking powder and flavoring.
Line jelly roll pan with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Turn out on dish towel that has been floured with powdered sugar. Fill with jelly, lemon pie filling or caramel condensed milk or your favorite filling and roll up.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients on warm heat to thicken, then whip applesauce and vanilla.
Add flour and white sugar.
Beat egg whites until foamy in another bowl.
Mix the 2 bowls together. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: scallops in tomato and paprika sauce
directions: If scallops are large, cut in 3 or 4 pieces.
If they are tiny bay scallops, leave them whole.
Heat the butter in a sautepan and add the scallops.
Cook, shaking the skillet or stirring, for about 2 minutes.
Remove from pan with a slotted spoon and set aside. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add the cognac or brandy to the pan and flambe.
Let flame until it dies out, without shaking the pan. Add the paprika; stir it through, then add the tomato sauce, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 3 or 4 minutes.
Return scallops to the pan and toss in the sauce.
Spoon into 4 to 6 scallop shells and top with cheese.
Place on a cookie sheet in a 400° oven and let heat just long enough to melt the cheese and heat the scallops through, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: pears antoine with sherbet
directions: Peel and core pears; slice into chunks.
Pour sherry into small bowl; add pears and marinate in refrigerator until serving time.
Place 1 scoop sherbet in each of 4 dessert dishes.
Spoon pear mixture on top and garnish with grated lemon peel.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda into large bowl. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Add egg, orange juice and orange peel all at once; stir just until mixture is evenly moist. Fold in raisins and cranberries. Spoon into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Remove and cool on rack. May use just cranberries instead of raisins.

title: sourdough coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into oiled 9-inch square pan. Prepare topping.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in Pyrex flat dish for 3/4 of an hour in moderate oven.
Use this like date and nut bread.
Spread with butter.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat at low speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into well greased tube or bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: healthy cookies
directions: Mix together and cook cookies 15 minutes at 350° on a cookie sheet.
Eat with milk for all four food groups.

title: cola salad
directions: Empty the jello into a bowl.
Add the boiling water; stir until the jello is completely dissolved.
Stir in the cola beverage.
Chill in the refrigerator or over ice and water until jello mixture is slightly thicker than consistency of thick, unbeaten egg white.
If chilled in the refrigerator, stir occasionally.
If chilled over ice and water, stir frequently.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Boil hen in water with salt.
Debone and reserve stock.
Melt butter in pot.
Blend in flour gradually with milk.
Then add broth and cook on low heat until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and add salad dressing, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix well.

title: lemon poppy-seed muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and poppy seed.
Add milk, lemonade, oil and egg whites.
Stir until moistened; do not overmix.
Coat a 12-muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray or line with muffin cups.
Fill each 2/3 full with muffin mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400° or until golden brown.

title: pain perdne(similar to french toast)
directions: Beat eggs; add evaporated milk and sugar and beat well. Grease iron skillet with butter/oleo.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture and fry in skillet until each side is golden brown. Sprinkle with a little powdered sugar or serve with syrup.
Makes 6 large portions.

title: chile burgers
directions: Mix in bowl.
Makes 4 patties.
Fry to desired doneness. Serve immediately.
Serves 4 persons.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix 1 can of asparagus, grated cheese, cream of mushroom soup and diced onion.
Spread bread crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Mix until well blended and set aside.

title: deer meat(steak or loin)
directions: You will also need a cast-iron skillet.

title: spiders
directions: Melt caramel chips and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Add Chinese noodles and salted peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Pour over cornflakes; mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: judy's shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Save 1 1/2 cups for toping.
Mix together molasses, soda and water.
Add crumbs; mix well.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Do not open oven during first 40 minutes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and mix. Knead on floured surface.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 8 big biscuits.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Fudge Frosting, if desired.
Cut into about 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies, 160 calories per brownie.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Measure milk in a 2 cup measure. Add oil and egg.
Blend well.
Make a well in center of flour mixture and pour in milk mixture all at once; stir quickly with a fork, just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Dip batter with a 1/4 cup measure, not quite full, and put into muffin cups.
The cups should be slightly more than half full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
Drain off water.
Drain juice from pineapple into small bowl.
Put pineapple in with carrots.
Put butter in carrots and let melt.
Take pineapple juice and add flour, heat until lumps are gone.
Put in carrots and heat on medium.
Cook until slightly thick.
Ready to serve.

title: italian braised beef
directions: Line a large Dutch oven with the strips of bacon.
Add the roast and brown on all sides over high heat.
Add the remaining ingredients; cover tightly and cook over low heat for 3 1/2 hours or until tender, turning occasionally.
Serve roast with the pot liquor and buttered pasta.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lavender punch
directions: Combine juice of lemon and orange, sugar, tartaric acid and boiling water.
Allow to stand for 24 hours.
Add cold water and grape juice.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Mix by wire whisk in order listed; refrigerate.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Add eggs, milk and oil. Beat just until smooth.(DO NOT OVERBEAT). Pour batter into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 425° for 25 min.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour together in pan. Beat egg yolks and add half & half. Add this to sugar mixture. Add half stick butter. Cook and stir until thick. Add vanilla and let cool. Pour into 8 inch pie shell and top with meringue.

title: 8-minute cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, vanilla and Cool Whip in bowl.
Pour into crust and garnish with strawberries.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: irene's beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: buster bar ice cream dessert
directions: Mix 1/3 cup butter, evaporated milk, chocolate chips and powdered sugar in a saucepan.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and cool.
Soften ice cream.
Crush oreo cookies and mix with 1/2 Cup melted butter.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cover with cheese. Bake until slightly brown, 10 or 15 minutes.

title: christmas nut roll
directions: Melt marshmallows (add a little water).
Cut gum candy, raisins, cherries and nuts.
Add to marshmallows.
Add graham cracker crumbs (1 1/2 bags).
Form into 2 rolls and roll in remaining graham cracker crumbs.
Wrap in wax paper and keep in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a jelly roll pan.
Mix together.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: red and green spread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together until smooth.
Stir in radishes and onions.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: lime marlowe
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package.
Add marshmallows while hot.
When ready to set, blend in cheese (it will look sort of lumpy).
Add remaining ingredients; let set.
This makes a pretty salad for Christmas.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding.
Add marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix and store for 3 hours.

title: surprise pie
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold in vanilla, crackers and nuts.
Pour into two greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and topping.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in 8-inch square baking dish. Cream the sugar and butter. Combine flavoring and milk and add alternately to creamed mixture with sifted dry ingredients.
Pour over fruit. Add Topping.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut into strips (2 x 1/4-inch).
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook meat in oil, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes for round steak, 5 to 8 minutes for steak.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes of simmering.

title: scalloped pineapple(microwave)
directions: Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup of juice.
Trim crusts from bread and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine pineapple, juice, bread and margarine (cut in 1/2-inch pieces).
Add beaten eggs, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased casserole.
Cover and microwave on High, 8 to 10 minutes, or until set.
Stir at 3 minute intervals.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy peanut butter cookies(makes about 5 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until very lightly browned (do not overbake).
Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Line baked, cooled pie shell with 2 cups of large, uncooked berries.
Make a sauce of the other 2 cups of berries.
Cut up and cook until thick with the sugar, water, cornstarch and salt. Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir well.
Cool.
Pour over berries in shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Spread with whipped cream.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Blend 1 tablespoon biscuit mix with 2 cans of cherry pie filling.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Do not grease.

title: coffee can bread
directions: You will need two 1 pound coffee cans.
Mix 2 cups flour with yeast.
Stir water, milk, butter, sugar and salt over low heat until butter melts.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add to flour and yeast.
Add remaining flour and eggs.
Dough will be stiff.
Knead on floured surface until dough is smooth and elastic.
Coat inside of each coffee can with small amount of oil.
Divide dough in half; place half in each can.
Cover with plastic tops.
Let rise in warm place until dough reaches about 1 inch from top.
Remove plastic and bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.
Can substitute molasses for sugar. Can brush outside with honey and sprinkle with slivered almonds after cooking.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Add buttermilk to have ingredients not too thick.
Melt butter in Pyrex dish (oblong). Pour half of melted butter in mixture.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 400° to 500° until light brown.

title: company cheesecake
directions: Add all ingredients together and press into a spring form pan. Set aside.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place chicken in a greased 8-inch square baking dish. In a saucepan, combine tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings; bring to a boil. Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken juices run clear. Sprinkle with cheeses; bake 10 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: summer dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: round steak
directions: Line the bottom of Dutch oven with bacon strips.
Peel and slice 1/2 of onion over bacon.
Peel and slice 2 potatoes over onion.
Cut steak in cubes and put a layer over potatoes, then sprinkle half pack of soup mix on steak.
Place remaining onion, potatoes and steak, then sprinkle with remainder of soup mix. Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter, sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk, mix well, add flour.
Add flavorings, mix well and pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake 325 °
for 1 hour 20 mins.

title: chili pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet until brown.
Drain. Stir in onion, tomatoes and seasoning mix (dry).
Spread in plate. Sprinkle with olives and cheese. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Serve with sour cream, shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice chantilly
directions: Combine rice, sour cream, salt and cheese.
Spread into buttered 1-quart dish. Bake about 5 minutes.
Take out and stir. Smooth out mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: fried rice
directions: In large skillet, heat oil; saute green onions until tender. Stir in rice and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally with a fork.
Push rice mixture to side of skillet; stir in eggs and pepper.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in peas.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with additional soy sauce, if desired.

title: herb marinated chicken breast
directions: Pour off fat, leaving the brown flecks.
Save the fat.
Add 1 cup of water and bring to a boil.
Measure into skillet 2 tablespoons of reserved fat for each cup of gravy desired.
Blend in equal amounts of flour or use half the amount cornstarch as you would use flour.
Stir over low heat until browned.

title: speedy ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in frying pan.
Add chili and tomato soups.
Bring to a simmer.
Add salt.
Line casserole with half the Fritos.
Pour in beef mixture; place remaining Fritos on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.

title: favorite cheese cake
directions: Blend and beat at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: hot tamales
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and taco flavor. Fry well. Add refried beans and mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam chopped broccoli 5 to 10 minutes; set aside.
Saute onions in 1/4 cup butter; saute cracker crumbs in 1/4 cup butter. Make sauce of soup, mushrooms and cheese.
When cheese is melted, add garlic, onions and almonds.
Place cooked broccoli in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over.
Combine sauteed cracker crumbs and almonds and sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: quick caramel cake
directions: Bake one cake mix according to package directions (your choice which flavor) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is baking, melt 14 ounce package of caramels.
Combine with 1 stick margarine and evaporated milk.
When cake is done, pour caramel mixture on top. You may sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans if desired.

title: pineapple beef teriyaki
directions: Heat wok or large skillet.
Add 1/4 cup vegetable and beef; cook until just done.
Remove meat from wok.
Add vegetables and cook until done, but still crisp.
Return meat to wok and season with soy sauce.
Serve over Polynesian fried rice.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, butter and 1 egg with mixer on medium speed.
Press into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Beat sugar, sour cream and 2 eggs until smooth and creamy.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; add 1/2 cup tomato sauce and stir well.
Shape into a 12 x 7-inch loaf; place on a lightly greased rack of broiler pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer 1/2 cake in bite size pieces in punch bowl, then 1/2 prepared pudding, 1/2 cherry pie filling, 1/2 crushed pineapple, 1/2 coconut and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: martha washington chocolates
directions: Mix all ingredients into very stiff dough. Roll into small balls. Let dry on wax paper. Dip in glaze.

title: fudge
directions: Spray 9 x 9 x 2 baking dish with nonstick coating. Melt chips, milk and honey in saucepan over medium heat until smooth. Remove from stove and stir in vanilla and nuts. Spread in baking dish. Cool and cut into squares.

title: pizza hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburg with salt and pepper; pat out into a 9-inch pie pan.
Spread tomatoes over hamburg and sprinkle with the cheese, parsley and onion.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Drain. Cut into wedges and serve.
(Bake at 375° in gas oven, 400° electric oven.)

title: beef and ham roll-ups
directions: *I usually buy the meat by the number of slices I need rather than by the pound.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Melt butter over high heat in skillet.
Add chopped garlic and juice of lemon to melted butter. Peel 1/2 of lemon and add peeling to butter mixture.

title: quick baked pike fillets
directions: For 4 servings, you will need:

title: broiled crab cakes
directions: Pick over crabmeat gently and carefully to remove shells and cartilage; do not break up lump meat.
Add seasoning, lemon juice, parsley and eggs; combine gently.
Form into medium-size cakes; place in lightly buttered flat pan.
Place under broiler; cook until golden brown, turning once.
Serve with salted crackers. Makes 4 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt oleo and mix with sugar and eggs.
Add 2 cups self-rising flour.
Combine with dissolved yeast mixture and add remaining flour.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin pan, about 3 tablespoons or No. 16 size scoop into pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remaining batter may be kept several days in refrigerator.
Makes 48 rolls.

title: lentil tomato salad
directions: Rinse lentils and place in a saucepan. Add water, salt and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered about 30 to 40 minutes until lentils are just tender. Drain.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon powdered mix.
Use 1/2 cup of mix per mug or glass of hot water.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and flavoring.
Pour in butter.
Add peaches to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Make pudding using 3 cups of milk.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Then layer more graham crackers and then more pudding.
Top with layer of graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top. Bake 325 until done (25 min.).

title: speed snack
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into glass and enjoy.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: play dough
directions: Bring to a boil the water, salt and food coloring.
Remove from heat and add flour, alum and cooking oil.
Mix; let cool. Knead after dough has cooled.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Beat eggs until light.
Beat in sugar 1 cup at a time.
Mix in flour.
Heat milk to boiling point, but do not boil.
Put butter in milk to melt.
Add flour mixture.
Add extracts.
Beat a few times.
Bake in two 9-inch pans for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spring breeze cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well. Spoon into crust.
Chill.
Garnish.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into small bite size balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and let cool.
Poke holes.
Heat pineapple and sugar.
Let cool. Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and seasoning mix together.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: fiesta potatoes
directions: Set oven controls to broil.
Spread hot potatoes in ungreased square 8 x 8 x 2 baking dish.
Spread with salsa.
Sprinkle with olives and cheese.
Broil with top 3 to 4 inches from heat until the cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with tortilla chips.
Serve with the remaining ingredients.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Mix with remaining ingredients except beef.
Crumble beef into mixture; mix thoroughly.
Press into 9 x 5-inch loaf dish.
Microwave on High until internal temperature reaches 150° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Rotate once or twice if you don't have turn table.
Spread on ketchup.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until ketchup is heated, 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: Combine all vegetables and elbows, then mayonnaise mixture.
If needed, add more mayonnaise to keep moist.

title: grandma's grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat eggs and vanilla.
Scald the milk and add to the egg mixture.
Add in first 3 ingredients.

title: freezer apple pie filling
directions: Peel, slice and core apples.
Combine sugar, flour and spices. Add sliced apples and toss gently.
Let stand 30 minutes until the juice begins to flow.
Stir in lemon juice; cook over low heat until it begins to thicken.
The apples should not be fully cooked.
Spoon into 6 to 8-pint freezer containers.
Plan on a quart to make a 9-inch pie and follow the oven time and temperature as for fresh apple pie.
I bake mine at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
I also top with a crumb topping.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 1/2 cup sugar three times.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff enough to hold shape.
Add vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Then fold in flour and sugar mixture.
Fold for 2 minutes.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
When done, invert pan to cool.

title: quick jam cake
directions: Put the ingredients listed in a large mixing bowl.
Blend on low speed of mixer until moistened.
Mix at medium speed for about 4 minutes.
Pour batter in prepared loaf pan (9 x 13-inch) or medium angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes.
Use Caramel Icing.

title: dell's one relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 50 minutes, stirring often.
Remove spice bag and put in jars and seal.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Put in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and chop eggplant.
Boil in salted water until tender; drain well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and bananas; beat well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt to the first mixture, then add milk and vanilla.
Beat well and stir in nuts. Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan lined on the bottom with waxed paper in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour.
Cool well and store airtight.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo.
Stir in shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Add seasonings and soup plus 1 can water. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir all of mixture into 2 cups cooked rice and serve.

title: dove paprika
directions: Brown pheasant pieces well in bacon drippings in deep pan. Add water, salt, pepper, bay leaves and garlic (minced).
Sprinkle in paprika.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until pheasant is tender; remove pheasant pieces from stock and set out 2 cups of gravy to cool.
Mix sour cream slowly with the cooled gravy (to prevent curdling) until smooth, then stir into the gravy in pan with cornstarch.
Return pheasant pieces to pan and reheat.
Serve with egg drop dumplings, mashed potatoes or brown rice.
Serves 4.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Combine potato flakes with chicken broth.
Melt oleo in saucepan; add flour and cook, stirring until flour is lightly browned.
Slowly stir in milk; keep stirring to make medium white sauce.
Add potato broth mixture and diced potatoes.
Add garlic powder, peppers, chives, parsley and salt.
Lop each serving with grated American cheese and bacon bits.

title: low-fat carrot-raisin salad
directions: In serving bowl, combine first 4 ingredients to make a smooth dressing.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.

title: spiced wieners
directions: Cut wieners to bite size and put into crock pot.
Pour salad dressing over wieners Cook 4 to 5 hours until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1 to 2 cups Cool Whip or enough for desired consistency.
Chill for about 30 minutes in covered dish before serving.

title: 9 day cole slaw
directions: Pour over cabbage, onion and pepper.
Mix well.
Will keep well when covered in refrigerator.

title: waverly cookies
directions: Line jellyroll pan with crackers (about 42 separated).
Melt margarine and butter.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and cook 2 minutes. Spread over crackers.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans on top.
Cook 10 minutes at 350°.
Place on waxed paper at once (they are sticky and cool quickly).

title: paulette's buttercream frosting
directions: Soften butter.
Add all ingredients and beat until creamy.

title: jay's nacho dip
directions: Add taco mix to hamburger and sausage. Add remaining ingredients to saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and is hot.
Keep warm in a crock-pot.
Eat with taco chips!

title: easy peanut butter pie
