directions: Mix all ingredients (1/2 of cool whip) well. Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with remaining cool whip. Sprinkle with grated nuts.

title: amy's cabbage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 12 x 9-inch covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sold at auction ambrosia
directions: Mix all together. Chill. Serve!

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix together rice, soup and water.
Pour in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice mixture.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creole pork chops(quick and easy)
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Sprinkle with rice, salt and pepper.
Top each with a green pepper ring.
Pour tomatoes over chops.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Roll dough out (1/4-inch thick) and top with filling. Roll filling and dough up like jelly roll; chill.
Slice and bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: creamed corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in a shallow baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until it tests done when a knife is inserted.

title: chicken and mushrooms dijon
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove.
In additional 1 tablespoon of margarine, cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid is evaporated; stir often.
Add soup, milk and mustard.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir often. Serve with noodles.
Serves 4.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup (Campbell's makes this soup now)

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft and drain off remaining water.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: turtle cake
directions: Pour half of cake batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt margarine, caramels and milk over low heat. Pour over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Add the rest of the batter and bake 20 minutes longer at 350°.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: african stew
directions: Brown beef in skillet then place in stew pot.
Add vegetables, tomatoes and spices.
Cook until tender. Add warm stew juice to the peanut butter.
Add mixture to stew pot.
Before serving, add condensed milk.
1/2 hour prep time.
1 1/4 hours cooking time.

title: canadian treat
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Add to cooled base.
Beat the milk and pudding mixes.
Let stand until thick, then spread over top of the base.
Add the other 1/2 of the Cool Whip and chill until ready to serve.

title: purple passion
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: all in one dinner in foil
directions: Get a piece of foil out big enough to seal all ingredients in.

title: sour cream cut-out cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir soda with whipping cream.
Add to sugar mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture.
Chill.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked beans on stove
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir all together and bake about 30 minutes in oven.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and pour off grease.
Mix meat with onion, soup, peas, salt and pepper.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with the mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: candy bar cookie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut cookie dough in half lengthwise. Cut each half into 12 slices.
Set aside.

title: baked crabmeat
directions: Mix and heat thoroughly.
Put in ramekins and sprinkle with grated cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. May be served on toast instead of baked.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of large jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch) with rolls, pressing together.
Bake at
350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, salad dressing and dressing mix. Spread on cooled baked roll dough and sprinkle with vegetables and cheese.
Press down so they stick.
Chill.
Cut in very small squares.
Enjoy!

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits until done.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add cheese, eggs and milk; stir until melted and smooth.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: carrot-banana bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy, then add bread and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except carrots and banana.
Mix together on low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in carrots and banana.
Pour mixture into a 7 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 2.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook butternut squash and mash (as in mashed potatoes).
Add butter, skim milk, egg whites and cinnamon.
Mash everything together.
Put in baking dish or Pyrex dish and bake for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup, then pour over hash browns (loose, not frozen together), chopped onions and cheese.
Toss together, then put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or oven dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
During last 7 to 10 minutes of baking, garnish with onion rings.

title: burgundy stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Mix all ingredients well in Dutch oven. Bake at 325° covered for 4 hours.
Serve in bowls over rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken, rice and broccoli casserole
directions: In a large pot, cook chicken.
Debone; set aside.
In a large skillet over medium heat, saut onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth. Place rice in a 11 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add chicken on top of rice.
Pour mixture in skillet over chicken.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Prep time:
45 minutes.

title: frozen party punch
directions: Combine water and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves. Add orange juice, pineapple juice, grapefruit juice and bananas. Pour into a container and freeze. Upon serving, put frozen mixture in punch bowl and ginger ale and stir to slushy consistency.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in pie shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken thoroughly.
Cook rice according to pkg. directions.
Chop chicken into fine pieces.
Combine chicken, rice, soups, and cheese in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
You can also use cream of onion soup instead of one of the other creamy soups if you want.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut up tomatoes.
Chop fine onions, peppers and celery.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer all 2 hours.
Process.

title: rich quick cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar in a heavy pan.
Add nuts; bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes, then cover graham crackers with the mixture.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Mix pudding, gelatin and water in saucepan; stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries. Chill until set.
Serve with whipped topping.
Garnish with strawberries.
This recipe is scrumptious.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute together butter, chopped onion, bell pepper, onion tops, parsley and garlic. Add pimentos, mushroom soup and Cheddar soup, heating thoroughly.
Add crawfish or shrimp and rice.
Pour into 12 x 12-inch casserole dish and top with crushed Escort crackers.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: apple muffins
directions: Stir together brown sugar, oil and egg.
Set aside.
Stir together milk, baking soda, salt, vanilla and add to brown sugar mixture alternating with 2 1/2 cup flour.
Fold in: 1 1/2 cup diced apple (don't peel) and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into tin and sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake at 325 for 30 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Add water to make brown gravy.
Cook over log fire for
4 weeks.
This
will
serve	3,800
people.	If more are expected, add
the
2 rabbits, but do this only if absolutely necessary, as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: hot tamale soup
directions: Heat heavy pan and add first 4 ingredients; cook until beef is browned.
Add chili powder, cumin, cayenne and cinnamon and cook 1 minute.
Add broth and tomatoes with juice.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Cream margarine until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Mix in margarine until smooth and creamy.
Mix in water, sweetener, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla extract.
Add to flour, margarine mixture.
Shape into balls. Place on cookie sheet; flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Yield:
24 cookies.
Carbohydrate 3.6 g, protein .5 g, fat 1.1 g, calories 30.
One cookie = 1/8 bread exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: snowdrops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip the egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar; continue whipping.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop in mounds on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Put in oven and turn off oven.
Leave in oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open door.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Two pieces of bread.
Add peanut butter and jelly.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Slice hard-cooked eggs in half, lengthwise.
Place yolks in mixing bowl and mix well.
Combine powdered mustard, salt, salad dressing, pickle relish and white pepper; mix until smooth.
Fill each cavity of egg white with yolk mixture.
Mound up slightly. Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with fine chopped parsley.

title: highland cookies
directions: Combine vinegar and milk and set aside.

Combine sugar and butter. Add eggs. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add alternately with milk and flavoring to the sugar and butter mixture. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: puddle cake
directions: Stir with a spoon.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted into the cake comes out cleanly.
A good eggless cake eaten plain, or dust with powdered sugar or top with frosting as desired.

title: date loaf
directions: Soak together the dates, bicarbonate of soda and the boiling water.
Cream margarine and sugar; beat in egg.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Add drained date mixture and stir well.
(Use liquid from date mixture until desired consistency.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash, onions, sour cream and soup.
In separate bowl, mix melted margarine and herb stuffing.
Place 1/2 in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread squash mixture over stuffing. Sprinkle remaining stuffing over squash.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Blend together milk, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm by adding water.
Add yeast and mix well.
Add egg.
Add flour gradually, mixing until dough is well blended.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush top with melted shortening and allow to rise until light.
Knead dough a few times to make smooth ball.
Form into desired shapes and bake in 400° oven for 15 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Easy and very tasty.

title: oreo cookie and cream surprise
directions: Crumb Mixture:
Crush cookies in a food processor or very fine by hand.
Set aside.

title: ginger tea punch
directions: Place tea bags and ginger in a tea pot. Add 4 1/2 cups boiling water. Cover; let steep 3 to 5 minutes or until desired strength. Remove tea bags. Stir in sugar. Cool at room temperature 2 hours. Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix lime juice and onion. Let stand for 30 minutes. Mix ketchup, cilantro and shrimp. Combine all and add as much salt and hot sauce as you like. Chill and serve.

title: catfish house mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil or boil until tomatoes are light green.
Do not continue to boil.
Gently stir a couple of times and seal in hot jars.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take out of oven and poke holes in the cake with a wooden spoon.
Pour milk in holes, then ice cream topping.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed candy bars.
Refrigerate.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: beth's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add warm milk and mix.
Microwave until thick or cook conventionally until boiling and thick.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash and onion; cook in a little water with salt, pepper and butter on low for 15 minutes.
Drain water; add sour cream and undiluted soup.
Add 1/2 cup butter to stuffing.
Add one-half of stuffing mixture to squash mixture, reserving one-half for top.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and sprinkle with remaining stuffing.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp-spinach crepe stack
directions: Prepare Creamed Spinach; set aside.
Heat oil in medium skillet over medium heat; add onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender.
Add mushrooms; cook until mushrooms are tender.
Continue cooking until moisture has evaporated.
Stir in Creamed Spinach, shrimp, lemon juice, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: frozen walnut salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, salt, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, bananas, walnuts and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour in pan or mold.
Freeze until firm.
We always have this at Christmas.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add boiling water and mix.
Add celery, cucumber, carrot, pepper, parsley and dill.
Mix in mayo, heavy cream, salt and salmon.
Mix well and chill overnight.
I use a fish mold.

title: wilted lettuce dressing
directions: Remove bacon from pan and break into small pieces.
Add to hot fat the vinegar, mustard (prepared) and mashed egg yolk.
Blend well.
Add bacon.

title: no beef meat loaf
directions: Mix the pork sausage, venison hamburger and egg.
Season with the chopped celery, onion, crushed sage and salt and pepper.
Put in 9-inch bread pan.
Cover with catsup.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: oatmeal-peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add applesauce; add sifted ingredients, oats and raisins.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's homemade ice cream mixture
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large pan.
Bring to a full boil.
After it cools down a bit, you may add fresh fruit of your choice or frozen fruit.
Just don't get too much syrup in the mix.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Over very low heat, melt chocolate.
Cool slightly.
In food processor, puree all ingredients except powdered sugar and chocolate.
Blend well.
Add melted chocolate and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until just set.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Boil carrots, cook and drain ground beef.
Use large kettle; add tomato sauce, soup, chopped onions and green beans.
After rolling out half of crescent rolls, place in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixture from kettle into casserole dish; lay cheese on top and the rest of rolled out crescent rolls.
Place in oven and bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain rice.
Add rice, drained tomatoes and sour cream.
Season to taste.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Spread cheese evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix in milk and vanilla; add flour and nuts and mix well.
Chill dough thoroughly; form into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: "chic's speciality" almond butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring occasionally to hard-crack stage (300°). Immediately spread on ungreased cookie sheet or 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Turn out on waxed paper.
Spread with chocolate and sprinkle with half of finely chopped nuts.
Set aside until chocolate is well set.
If necessary, chill to set chocolate.
Turn and coat other side with chocolate and nuts. Break into pieces when cooled and dry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, margarine and corn syrup.
Pour over pecans.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind and mix cranberries, orange and sugar, then let set.
Mix strawberry Jell-O, orange Jell-O, hot water, cold water and sugar. Put in refrigerator until it starts to jell, then mix everything together and let set overnight.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except Sweet and Sour Sauce and parsley; shape into 20 meatballs and place in baking pan.
Bake meatballs in preheated 350 degree oven until browned and no longer pink in center, about 20 minutes.
Arrange meatballs in serving dish; pour hot Sweet and Sour Sauce over meatballs and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar, cocoa, salt and water.
Add evaporated milk and bring to boil.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.

title: glazed fruit dessert(serves 6)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine pudding and pineapple juice.
Stir until thickened.
Fold in oranges, pineapple and bananas. Refrigerate until serving.
Garnish with a dollop of whipped topping.

title: surprise pie
directions: Mix ingredients; press into 8 x 10-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: layer dinner casserole
directions: Place in a buttered casserole the chopped onions, celery, potatoes and ground beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour tomato juice over top and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: cream filled oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, soda and cinnamon; add to mixture.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on waxed paper.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cook in double boiler or crock-pot for 1 hour all ingredients, except broccoli.
Add the broccoli.
Use as dip for crackers or nachos.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Turn into 2 large cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven. Cool completely.
Break apart.

title: stained glass candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo in double boiler, then cool. Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallows.
Mix until all coated. Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle with coconut and roll with mix.
Prepare four (12-inch) strips of foil; roll mix in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 4 logs of candy.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: In a large saucepan on the conventional range top surface unit bring 6 cups of water and 1 teaspoon of salt to boiling point.
Add 8 cabbage leaves; simmer about 2 or 3 minutes, just long enough to make leaves pliable.
Drain leaves on paper towels.
Cook beef in a glass utility dish using microwave for 4 minutes.
Mix together lightly, in a medium-size mixing bowl, ground beef, cooked rice, minced onion, egg and poultry seasoning.
Form meat mixture into 16 even balls.
Cut the core out of the cabbage leaf.
Fill the center of each cabbage leaf with 2 meat balls.
Fold 2 sides of leaf over meat balls and roll up leaves from the end.
Arrange cabbage rolls, seam side down in a 2-quart glass utility dish.
Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, water and lemon juice or vinegar together in 2-cup glass measuring cup or small mixing bowl.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Place wax paper over dish.
Cook with microwave 10 minutes. Allow cabbage rolls to stand 10 minutes with covering before serving.
Recipe yields 8 servings.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Microwave or cook the 2 cans of potatoes in a saucepan until completely warm. Add Ranch dressing. Cook again until warm. Add the bacon bits and shredded cheese. Cook for 2 minutes, until the cheese is melted.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter, salt and vanilla in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and nuts.
Drop stacks on wax paper.
Let stand until cool.

title: orange sugar pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until soft ball stage. Add 1 pound shelled pecans; stir until it begins to sugar.
Pour out on wax paper and break apart.

title: fritter batter for deep frying
directions: Combine eggs, milk, and butter in bowl.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, and sugar.
Stir just until moistened.
Use for coating vegetables, onion rings, fish, and chicken for deep frying.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening; add sugar.
Add enough flour to thicken like gravy.
Mix in dissolved yeast; add flour until dough is quite firm.
Use more flour if needed, or less.
Cover and let stand about 15 minutes.
Roll out and cut with rim of small glass.
Fold circle over and dip in melted butter.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Place in cold oven and turn on to 400° and bake about 15 minutes, until light brown.

title: no bake cherry confetti pie
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; stir in pie filling.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon ingredients into baked pie shells.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Yields 2 pies.
(Another good, easy company dessert!)

title: eclair delights
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk until thick, then add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Put a layer of graham crackers on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, then half of pudding mixture, another layer of graham crackers and rest of pudding mixture.

title: chicken cordon bleu casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish. Line pan with chicken breasts. Top this with layer of ham, then Swiss cheese. Combine soup and water; spread over cheese layer.

Sprinkle stuffing over soup mixture. (May also sprinkle packet of herbs and seasonings if with stuffing.) Melt margarine and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with foil for about the first 45 minutes, then uncover to brown.

title: bierocks
directions: Brown ground beef or pork and onion in oven.
Add cabbage. Cover and cook in oven 7 to 8 minutes.
Add cheese and seasonings and mix well.

title: pockets of pizza
directions: Unroll refrigerated pizza crust.
Press out to a 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut into four pieces.
Top one side of dough with shredded Mozzarella cheese along with your favorite pizza toppings.
Fold dough over filling.
Pinch and seal edges.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spritzgeback(butter nut cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter cookie sheet.
Whip butter and sugar together until well blended.
Add vanilla, egg yolks and rum.
Add flour and ground almonds, blending gently with spatula. Fill pastry bag with dough and form small circular shapes, approximately 2-inches apart on the cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check after 10 minutes.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: skillet bacon-onion biscuits
directions: Combine eggs and tomato juice or milk in mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl and beat until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot, well-greased skillet.
Sprinkle top of each biscuit with chopped onion and bacon.
Cook over moderate heat about 5 minutes until lightly browned on one side.
Turn and brown other side.
Makes 8 to 12.

title: cold water chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and eggs together. Sift all dry ingredients together; slowly add dry ingredients to creamed butter and eggs. Add 1 cup cold water and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: picnic wheel meat patties
directions: Boil onions until tender; drain thoroughly.
Force through sieve.
Combine onions with meat, parsley, crumbs, egg, cheese and seasonings.
Shape into 48 small patties.
Pan-fry in shallow hot oil; drain on absorbent paper.
Do not pack for the picnic until thoroughly cold.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, omitting salt.
Drain well.
Place broccoli in baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese.
Add milk and egg. Pour over broccoli.
Combine herb dressing and butter.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.

title: amandel brood(almond bread)
directions: Soak cereal in milk for 1 hour.
Mix together with rest of ingredients.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Bring
sugar, vinegar, water and mustard to a boil and cool.

title: chocolate crunch cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Gradually add the flour; dissolve soda in hot water and add with vanilla to dough.
Fold in the nuts and chocolate bits.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken supreme dijon
directions: In large skillet cook chicken in butter.
Remove to heated platter.
Keep warm.
To drippings in pan add garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring, until onion is tender.
Stir in mustard and heavy cream.
Simmer, stirring, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Add chicken, turning to coat in sauce.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: sausage-cheese balls(makes 75 appetizers.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients until dough sticks together.
Roll in 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake about 25 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm on toothpicks.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Brown onions in butter and oil.
Add corn, tomatoes and olives; cook 15 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add eggs, milk and meal and cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add all remaining ingredients and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake and garnish with whole ripe olives.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: corn spoon bread casserole
directions: Combine eggs, muffin mix, cream-style corn, whole kernel corn, sour cream and butter.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Put grated cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: strawberry soup
directions: In food processor, puree the strawberries.
Add cider or apple juice, cinnamon, honey, sugar and nutmeg.
Just prior to serving, whisk in cream and wine.
Serve in chilled glass bowls.
Garnish with strawberry slices and sour cream.

title: missouri venison stew
directions: Remove sinews and bones from venison; cut meat into bite-size pieces and roll in flour.
Brown in hot bacon fat in deep kettle. Add hot water, wine, herbs, onions and salt and pepper.
Cover pot and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, adding more hot water, if needed.
When meat is tender and vegetables done, serve hot. Serves 6.

title: no bake strawberry or blackberry icebox pie
directions: Clean berries.
Set aside.
In bowl, mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
After well blended, add berries (strawberries sliced and blackberries whole).
Put in baked pie shell.
Pour whipped whip cream on top of pie.
Refrigerate.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sherbet and 1/2 of ice cream.
Beat until smooth.
Add 7-Up.
Spoon remaining ice cream into punch. Serve immediately.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup, butter and salt.
Put over medium heat and cook until dissolved.
While this is cooking, beat eggs until they foam.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm water; let sit. Mix egg, sugar, shortening, flour and hot water. Add yeast mixture.
Add flour; work dough.
Brush top with oil; cover with cloth. Let rise until double in size. After dough rises, may refrigerate until ready to use.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten in desired. Notice no flour in this recipe.
Great taste.

title: marshmallow sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet
potatoes
until
tender,
remove
skins and mash. Add butter, milk, salt, cinnamon or nutmeg and paprika. Beat until free
from	lumps
and
light
and fluffy.	Fold in walnuts.
Turn into a greased casserole, cover with marshmallows and bake
in
a moderate
oven
until mixture is heated through and marshmallows are brown.
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans
as directed on package.
Drain well.
Make a paste of the flour and butter, adding the salt, sugar and onion. Add the sour cream and cheese.
Gently fold in green beans and spoon into casserole.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: health bread
directions: Boil and cool the raisins and water.
Mix well and bake in a small loaf pan 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, oleo and milk rapidly for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Fold until melted.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tomato, onion and zucchini salad
directions: Place alternating slices of tomatoes, zucchini and onion on serving platter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Whisk together oil and vinegar and pour over salad.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, but not more than 4 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 3 hours; serve.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop by 1/2 teaspoon in deep fryer.

title: work person's roast
directions: Place roast in center of large sheet of foil.
Cut slits in roast and insert garlic.
Pour mushroom soup over top, then pour Worcestershire sauce over soup.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over top and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add meat tenderizer according to cut of meat.
Pull foil up and seal lightly, leaving space around roast.
Put roast in cake pan and put in oven at 250° from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m.
Crock-pot can be used and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: layered peppermint pie
directions: Layer 13 cookies in bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan. Combine milk and water with electric mixer; beat in pudding mix until blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Stir in the 3/4 cup crushed candy.
Beat cream until stiff.
Reserve 1/2 cup for garnish.
Fold remaining whipped cream into pudding mixture.
Pour half of mixture over cookies; repeat layers.
Garnish with whipped cream and candies.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit.
Keep in the refrigerator at all times for the family to eat.
It is wonderful.
Just keep on adding cut-up fruit.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: In a large saucepan, add margarine, oil, cocoa and water. Bring to a boil, stirring as not to scorch.
Take from heat and pour in sugar, sifted with plain flour and stir.
Add buttermilk with 1 teaspoon soda stirred in.
Add beaten eggs, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased oblong pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican cole slaw
directions: Combine vegetables.
Combine salt, pepper, vinegar, oil and pickles.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Can be served on lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: german molasses cakesor sho-fly pie
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and take out 1 cup of batter (set aside for topping).

title: cara and megan's flat bread
directions: Thaw bread dough according to package directions on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Press thawed dough into a rectangle about 8 x 16-inch.
Prick top of bread with a fork.
Brush with oil.
Sprinkle to taste with salt and thyme. Bake 15 to 18 minutes, until golden.
Serve warm.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Put red pepper and green pepper and a little vinegar in blender and blend.
Pour into a saucepan and add the rest of the vinegar and the sugar.
Bring to a fast boil.
Add Certo and stir one minute.
Bring to boil again and skim foam.
Boil for 1 more minute and add food coloring.
Remove from heat and cool.
Put in jars and seal.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and cover each piece with a slice of cheese.
Spread soup over cheese and stuffing mix over soup. Pour melted butter over stuffing.
Bake at 325° approximately 45 minutes or until done.

title: church baked beans
directions: Drain cup of liquid off pork and beans.
Chop onions and mix along with all other ingredients to beans.
Mix well.
Add strips of bacon to top of beans.

title: chocolate fudge squares
directions: Mix as usual (no liquid).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven.
*Pour marshmallows over hot cake layer and top with Fudge made as follows:

title: spiral mix
directions: Mix all together and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: strawberry pretzel pudding
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: the best of the chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruitcake cookies(very good)
directions: Cream butter,
sugar and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients alternately
with milk.
Mix chopped fruits and nuts in (after they have
been
dredged in flour.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: turkey and wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Cook 2 minutes, until onion is translucent.
Add water and broth.
Stir in rice mix and seasoning packet; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, until rice is tender.
Add sherry and boil for 1 minute, then add turkey.
Reduce heat to low.
Mix cream and egg yolk.
Stir in a few spoonfuls of soup.
Add mixture to soup in saucepan in a slow, steady stream, stirring constantly.
Cook only until slightly thickened and hot; do not boil!
Makes 4 servings.

title: hummus bi tahini
directions: Put all ingredients into a food processor with a metal blade. Process to make a smooth paste.
Add additional liquid, if needed. Serve in bowl with pita wedges.

title: chocolate mountains
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Add melted chocolate and melted additional fat.
Add nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Top with candied cherries.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: easy sweet bread
directions: Combine these ingredients and add to yeast mixture.
Divide into 4 well-greased loaf pans.
Dough will be sticky.
After bread rises, brush with egg wash (1 egg, beaten, 1 tablespoon milk) and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cool.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Combine fruit with sugar, juice and all.
Cook 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars.
Either refrigerate or freeze.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: Boil water and mix in sugar and coffee.
Cool liquid and add brandy.
Pour liquid into a jar.
Drop in the vanilla bean.
Seal and let it stand for at least 30 days.

title: lemon cake-pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and butter. Add lemon juice, lemon rind, egg yolks and milk. Mix. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased casserole (Pyrex).
Bake in pan of hot water at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, dessert will have custard on bottom and sponge cake on top.
(Use whipped cream or Cool Whip on top when served, if you like.) Serves 8.

title: crazy peach pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, buttermilk, salt and baking soda.
Pour over melted margarine in a large baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Pour fruit over top, juice and all (do not mix.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and solid.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread the bean dip on a large platter.
Spread the guacamole dip over beans.
Mix the sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add the taco seasoning mix.
Spread this mixture as the next layer.
Refrigerate for a few hours and it will become firm.
Right before serving, top with a layer of chopped black olives, chopped tomatoes and cover with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Fritos and taco chips.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put asparagus into 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cup bread crumbs and half of cheese on top.
Pour diluted, warmed mushroom soup over this.
Do not stir.
Pour peas and then add remainder of cheese in next layer.
Then add remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: wendy's easy pot pie
directions: Cook chicken. Cool and chop. Mix chicken with cream of celery and cream of chicken soups and the Veg-All. Put mixture into pie crust. (I use Pillsbury pie crust that comes 2 to a box in the dairy section.) Put other pie crust on top. Pinch crust together. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and pimento for 1 hour.
Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil.
Pour sauce over vegetables and store in refrigerator overnight with a tight lid.
Take out next day and drain sauce.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and pie filling together; set aside.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place miniature marshmallows in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as per directions.
Spread the mixed cake dough over marshmallows.
Spoon Jell-O and fruit mixture over cake dough in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: homemade pumpkin pie
directions: Pumpkin:
Wash and clean inside.
Slice it up and peel it. Drop into boiling salty water.
Cook until tender.
Drain it and mash it.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients in order listed. Cook and stir until sauce comes to a full boil. Pour into a bowl to use with appetizers.

title: amish pineapple
directions: Pour half and half over bread crumbs and let stand.
Cream butter and sugar together; beat in eggs.
Fold in a large can pineapple.
Add bread cubes soaked in half and half.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into bowl.
Add shortening, milk and peanut butter.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add milk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour cake mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or 30 to 35 minutes in layer pans.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, oil and zucchini; mix well.
Add 1 cup of chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift flour and cocoa together and add alternately with buttermilk (to which you have added soda and vanilla).
After mixing well, fold in coconut and beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased, floured and wax paper lined 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cake will fall slightly when cool.

title: "garlic-n-herb potatoes"
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour oil in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Add garlic, stirring to coat.
Heat pan in oven for 5 minutes. Add rosemary and potatoes to pan, stirring to coat.

title: coconut icebox cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions using a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix the sugar and milk and bring to a boil. Stir in 1 package coconut and then pour over the cake while it's still hot. Cover cake tightly until cool.
When cool, spread whipped topping over cake and sprinkle with other package of coconut.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: apricot melon cooler
directions: Remove seeds and rind from melon.
Cut into pieces, enough to make one cup.
Set aside.
Pour the nectar, lemon juice and dash of salt into electric blender container.
Cover and turn on motor, gradually adding melon pieces.
Add in order the ice cubes and the lemon sherbet.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
Serve immediately.

title: garlic butter(3 pound recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly until whipped smooth.
Put into container and refrigerate.
Use as needed.

title: chili bean casserole
directions: Butter large casserole and line with crushed corn chips.
Heat chili and beans.
Alternate layers of beans, chili, onion, corn chips and cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven for about 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandmommie's italian meat balls
directions: Mix everything together and shape into balls.
Use your "special" sauce.

title: pork sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients for 45 minutes and then strain.
Makes one gallon.

title: upside down cherry pie
directions: Melt butter in loaf pan.
Blend flour, sugar and baking powder in bowl.
Blend
eggs
in milk and make batter of flour and sugar mixture.
Pour
batter in loaf pan with butter, then add the can of
cherry
pie filling and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until
a
toothpick inserted in crust comes out dry.
Serve in the loaf pan, to be dipped into bowls.

title: sausage pitas
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 2 tablespoons butter; add kielbasa cut in 1/4-inch slices and the drained sauerkraut.
Heat.
Mix in sour cream and mustard.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve in pita pockets.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, dressing and flavor packets from noodles together, microwave for 30 seconds, and refrigerate.
Crush noodles and mix with slaw mix, sunflower seeds and broccoli in a large bowl.
Pour liquid over salad mix and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thick, about 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.
In a saucepan, heat milk and butter just until butter melts, stirring occasionally. Add to batter, beating until combined.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except black-eyed peas and grated cheese.
Add the black-eyed peas and grated cheese and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: snap bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn in casserole dish.
Mix soup, cream cheese, salt and pepper and pour on top of bean mixture, spreading evenly. Mix melted butter and crushed crackers and spread on the top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix according to package directions.
While hot, prick top with fork or toothpick.
Pour Kahlua over top and cool. Break brownies into pieces.
Make mousse according to package directions.
Crush Heath bars.
Layer brownie pieces, mousse and Heath bars.
Save some mousse for topping.
You may be able to get 2 to 3 layers.
Top with whipped cream and crushed Heath bars. Serve in crystal or fancy bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps 4 to 5 days (if it lasts that long).

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mixer. Pour into the freezer can. Finish filling the freezer can with milk and then freeze.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Pour hot water over Shredded Wheat; add molasses, salt and shortening.
Let cool.
Add yeast mixture; let rise.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead and let rise twice in size. Put in pans; let rise.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mari lynn's ground beef casserole
directions: Combine meat,
egg,
of
onion,
green
pepper and crackers.
Mix well.
Line 1 1/2-quart casserole with mixture, pressing evenly
over
bottom
and	up sides.
Combine 2/3 cup water and
margarine.
Heat until margarine melts.	Add stuffing mix and
other half of onion and celery.
Mix well.
Spoon into center
of	casserole.
Spoon soup over top.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350° oven 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 5 servings. Good!

title: french toast casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 of bread cubes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cube cream cheese and place over bread.
Layer remaining 1/2 of bread cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and syrup.
Pour over cheese and bread. Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Cook next morning at 350° for 45 minutes.
Excellent for Christmas morning breakfast.
Warm syrup and serve over casserole.

title: quick pizza sauce
directions: Cook all the ingredients together about 1/2 hour over slow heat. Add 1/4 cup grated Italian Parmesan cheese and use on any pizza dough.

title: spicy shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter in a Dutch oven until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, oregano, thyme and red pepper.
Cook over medium heat stirring occasionally about 15 minutes or until desired consistency.
Stir in shrimp and simmer over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin square bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and soda. Add pumpkin, oil and vanilla. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one. Mix together well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased and floured jelly roll pan.

title: michelle's cookie recipe
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place dough on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Take cookies out while they are still gooey.
If overbaked, cookies will be hard in the morning.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture.
Mix in walnuts and dates.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°, until top has dull crust.

title: hungry jack best casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half and form half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.

title: plum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Start mixture; add oil, sugar, plum baby food, vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and spices and add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet in hot oil cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top each chicken piece with lemon slice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally. Yields 4 servings.

title: milky way cake
directions: Mix candy, butter and pecans together; heat until melted. Combine rest of mix together.
Fold in candy mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread candy quickly in 9 x 5-inch dish.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: bacon cheese dogs
directions: Cut halfway through the hot dog slices.
Place cheese slice in each; wrap with 1/2 slice bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and browns.

title: salmon patty cakes
directions: Save salmon juice; remove most of the bones.
Scramble eggs well.
Put the salmon in bowl with onion, bread crumbs and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
If dry, pour a little juice from the salmon into mix.
Make small patties (about 8).
Fry 10 pieces of fat back meat; save grease.
Fry 4 cakes at a time until golden brown.
Eat it by itself or serve over rice or make sandwich.
Makes about 8 cakes.

title: ed's delicious quick-beans
directions: Note:
These beans will come out best if boiled in a ceramic or stoneware beanpot, but if you don't have one, just use a deep casserole dish with lid.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add soups.
Brown the Tater Tots in the oven.
Pour sausage, soup and cheese in casserole dish.
Layer Tater Tots on top; cook in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Grease dish with spray Pam.
Pour the first 4 ingredients into dish.
Top with bacon, cut up.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Great with ham.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Pour scalded milk and oils over dry ingredients; stir together.
Knead and let rise.
Knead and let rise again.
Knead and put in pans.
Pam the loaf; dust with corn meal.
Put Pam in bread pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet corn for freezer
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Cool well and put into freezer bags.
This is very good and tastes like fresh corn.

title: "mom's" meatloaf
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients.
Add desired amount of milk for proper consistency (approximately 1/4 cup milk). Top with ketchup and brown sugar if desired.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg, milk and flavoring.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours.
Roll 1/8 inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Cut into shapes with floured cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a moderate 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a casserole.
Add slivered almonds. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix this with other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and microwave.
Serve with crackers.

title: boeuf bourguignon
directions: Brown meat.
Put into casserole.
Make gravy.
Can add bouillon cubes for flavor.
Pour over meat and add Burgundy wine. Put in oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
One hour before serving, add mushrooms and some more Burgundy wine.
Serve over rice or wide noodles.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift flour and then measure.
Cream butter and sugar (a long time for finer texture).
Add eggs, one at
a time.
Add milk and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan.

title: america's favorite pot roast
directions: Trim all excess fat from roast, brown if using chuck or another highly marbled cut.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coal meat with the flour mixture.
Place all vegetables except mushrooms in crock-pot and top with roast (cut roast in half, if necessary, to fit easily).
Spread mushrooms evenly over top of roast.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 10 hours.
If desired, turn to high setting during last hour to soften vegetables and make a gravy.
To thicken gravy, make a smooth paste of the 3 tablespoons flour and the water and stir into crock-pot.
Season to taste before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as instructed on back of box.
Grease 14 x 18-inch cookie sheet. Pour in cake mixture.
Bake as directed until fork comes out clean.

title: indian chicken
directions: Note:
Small amounts of chopped parsley, onion, celery and green pepper are good.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick; let cool.
Cream 10x sugar, Crisco, margarine and vanilla together, then mix with cooled ingredients and beat 10 minutes.
Refrigerate.
Good on top of yellow cake with strawberries.

title: ziti with sausage and cream sauce
directions: Heat butter and oil in large frying pan.
Add onion and saute for 2 minutes.
Add sausage and cook, crumbling with fork, for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Reduce heat to low and add cream, salt and pepper.
Continue to cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens; do not boil.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Place peaches in crust.
Combine 1 cup sugar. 1/3 cup flour and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream, stirring until well blended. Spoon over peaches.
Combine sugar and 1/2 cup flour; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over pie. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or golden brown.
Us sliced peach to garnish.

title: veggie squares
directions: Press crescent rolls into jelly roll pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix the Miracle Whip, cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread on top of cooled rolls.
Top with any combination of chopped veggies.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice enough cucumbers to make 1 gallon.
Soak cucumbers and onions in salt water and ice cubes for 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drain cucumbers and onions; add to the mixture. After boiling for 1 minute, put in jars and seal.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: salmon pate
directions: Make sure salmon is free of bones and skin.
Put cooked salmon
and the rest of the ingredients into a food processor. Process until well mixed.
Refrigerate.
Serve as a cracker spread or as a sandwich.

title: honey mustard dip for chicken nuggets
directions: Mix together and use.

title: no cook fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spread into a 9-inch square pan.
Let set until firm; cut and serve.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins and dates in water.
Cook until water is gone. Mix raisins, dates, eggs, applesauce and oil.
Add nuts and mix rest of ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or stem pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: banana brunch punch
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend bananas, orange juice and lemonade until smooth.
Remove half of the mixture and set aside.
Add 1 1/4 cups of warm water and 1 cup sugar to mixture in blender; blend until smooth.
Place in a large freezer container. Repeat with remaining banana mixture, water and sugar; add to container.
Cover and freeze until solid.
One hour before serving, take punch base out of freezer.
Just before serving, place in a large punch bowl.
Add pineapple juice and soda; stir until well blended.
Garnish with orange slices if desired. Yields 16 to 20 servings (3 quarts).

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken
to 25 minutes.
Peel skin off.
Pick chicken
off
bone
and
chop up.
Dip tortillas in water from boiled chicken.
Line
in
bowl
or a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix onions,
cheese,
tomatoes, chili powder and garlic salt. Layer chicken on tortillas.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Mix 2 cans
of soups together and spread over top of chicken.
Bake at
for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.

title: williamsburg inn honey sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and boil 3 minutes; cool, then add next 4 ingredients.
Pour over fresh fruit.

title: kiwi and grape rice pudding
directions: Put milk and sugar in a saucepan and heat until small bubbles form around pan's edge.
Stir in rice and cook, covered, over lowheat about 45 minutes or until rice is tender and most of the milk is absorbed.
Stir in vanilla, kiwi and grapes.
Put into dessert glasses, garnish with kiwi and serve warm.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for pie.
In medium pan, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in oregano, salt, pepper, crumbs, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, onion and green pepper. Turn into pie crust.
Spread cheese topping over filling.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Stir together remaining tomato sauce and the chili sauce.
Serve with pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese; combine with cream cheese and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape mixture as a ball; roll over pecans.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add garlic and saute on low heat until soft.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Stuff each shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: freida's fried chicken fingers
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Cut chicken into bite size strips. Combine egg, salt, pepper, mustard and ketchup in bowl.
Stir.
Dip cut up chicken in mixture and coat with flour.
Place in hot oil; fry until done, approximately 5 minutes.
Serve with ketchup or barbecue sauce for dipping.

title: vegetable lasagna(eating light)
directions: Cook lasagna noodles; drain and set aside.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, cottage cheese, Ricotta and Italian seasoning; set aside.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: First day, pack cucumbers
in
jar longways.
Mix 1 cup plain salt and 1/2
gallon boiling water; pour over cucumbers. On second day, pour off water and rinse good.
Add 1 jar alum. Cover with boiling water.
On	third
day,
pour off water and rinse good. Add plain boiling water.
On the fourth day, pour off water, then mix
spices
in
bag
with 1/2 gallon vinegar. Boil together.
Add to cucumbers and let stand for 7 days.
On eighth day, take out of vinegar and slice.	Put cucumbers back in jar.
Add sugar until enough syrup covers cucumbers.

title: easy sherbet punch
directions: Put sherbet into punch bowl and place in refrigerator to thaw. Just before serving, remove bowl from refrigerator and add ginger ale, slowly, stirring well.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, together.
Pour over crackers.
Stir occasionally for 2 hours.

title: very special pork chops
directions: Brown chops in fat in heavy skillet; pour off drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Cook over low heat about 1 hour or until chops are tender and sauce has thickened.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: french fried mushrooms (or dill pickles)
directions: Dip mushrooms into milk; dip into pancake mix.
Fry in oil at 375° for 2 minutes or until golden brown; drain on paper towels.

title: rosy strawberry ring
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring occasionally, until thawed.
Stir in pineapple, bananas and lemon juice.
Pour into dish or mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving platter. Decorate with sprigs of mint.
Serve with Dressing.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef in the water until almost done.
Add all other ingredients except potatoes.
Cook 1 1/2 hours until vegetables are tender.
Add potatoes and cook until they are done.
More water may be added, but a good rich broth is very important to taste well.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients and add beaten egg.
Drop by tablespoon in greased frying pan.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: caramel corn
directions: Butter the sides of a saucepan.
Combine butter, sugar and syrup.
Stir well and bring to hard ball stage.
Take off heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn to coat.

title: basic tomato meat sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in saucepot.
Add onion and cook until lightly browned.
Add and brown ground chuck.
Add slowly, a mixture of tomatoes, salt, bay leaf and sweet basil or oregano.
Cover saucepot and simmer over very low heat about 2 1/2 hours.
Add tomato sauce.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain cherry juice and add sugar; boil 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water to both packages of Jell-O in a bowl.
Add cherry and sugar juice to Jell-O.
Add Coca-Cola, mix well and add cherries and pecans.
Put in icebox to jell.

title: can't leave alone bars
directions: Mix with fork the cake mix, oil and eggs.
This will form a ball like pizza dough.
Pat half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, ungreased.
Melt in saucepan the butter, condensed milk and chocolate chips.
Put over cake mixture and then put rest of cake mixture on top.
Swirl with knife. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Rich, chewy and utterly delicious!

title: marshmallow dip
directions: Mix together and serve. Good with fruit!

title: pork chop skillet
directions: Brown
pork
chops
in skillet;
remove.
Add onion and brown. Add
Minute rice and water.
Salt and pepper to taste. I also use
Cavender's
Greek seasoning.
Place pork chops on top of this mixture.
Cover and steam for 30 minutes.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Mix oleo, crackers and sugar and put into 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Dream Whip and spread over cracker crumbs.
Cover with your favorite pie filling and put in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 375°.

title: polenta in microwave
directions: Mix together cornmeal and cold water and add hot water and margarine.
Mix well.
Microwave 4 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 to 3 minutes more.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Brown veal and onion; add tomatoes, water and soup and heat. Put in baking pan, cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Uncover and put cheese on meat; warm until melted.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar; cool until syrupy, then beat until fluffy.
Whip the chilled evaporated milk.
Add the lemon juice.
Fold into first mixture.
Combine crushed vanilla wafers with the melted butter.
Line pan with crumb mixture.
Add jello mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pineapple tea
directions: Mix in punch bowl.
Great to serve at showers.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: german apfel kuchen(apple cake)
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add 1/3 cup of sugar, 1 egg and the lemon peel.
Press into a ball.
Roll out on floured surface. Line bottom and partially up sides of a greased 12-inch spring-form pan with the dough.
Decoratively lay apples on pastry and bake for 35 minutes.
In a medium bowl, beat 3 eggs, cream, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Pour over apples and bake for 20 to 25 minutes until custard is set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Make balls about 1-inch.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken perigod style
directions: Brown cutlets on all sides in 6 tablespoons margarine, until brown.
Take out of pan, add 2 tablespoons margarine, add mushrooms.
Brown about 5 minutes.
Take out of pan.
Into pan over medium heat, stir in flour and salt until blended.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and half and half milk.
Stir constantly until thick.
Put chicken broth in pan with mushrooms and simmer for 25 minutes, until cooked.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: corn crisped chicken
directions: Mix the crumbs and seasonings together.
Dip chicken in the milk and roll in the crumb mixture until well coated.
Place in a shallow foil-lined baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is an easy way to cook chicken for a large group.

title: low-cal meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour off excess fat.

title: teresa's cake
directions: Bake white cake as directed.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk.
Spread on cake.
Drain pineapple and spread over cake. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: blueberry swirl pie
directions: Mix and
press
in
9-inch pie pan; bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Form ball and put back in refrigerator to set.

title: goody-good pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla, pecans and raisins.
Spoon into 2 (9-inch) loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: baked salmon patties
directions: Remove skin and partially drain salmon. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spoon into greased muffin pans, using 1/4 c. mixture in each muffin cup. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: turkey milanese
directions: Sprinkle turkey cutlets with salt and pepper.
In bowl, beat egg whites.
On plate, mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Coat cutlets with egg whites and then crumb mixture.
Fry in skillet over medium-high heat with olive oil for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Serve with lemon.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Combine vegetables, soup and chicken. Pour into pie shell. Chop boiled egg over chicken mixture. Mix egg, milk and Bisquick mix, then pour over top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: ice box banana chocolate pie - no bake
directions: Method:
Slice banana on bottom of pie crust.
Add prepared pie filling.
Add chunks of chocolate bar if desired.
Let filling set.

title: blow-out cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Beat peanut butter and butter until fluffy.
Add both sugars and beat until light and smooth.
Add egg and beat 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in flour and beat thoroughly.
Sprinkle milk over mixture and beat to soften the dough.
Fold in chocolate chips and peanuts, then carefully add the candy.
Drop by 2 tablespoons clumps on ungreased baking sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until just browned.
Makes about 30.

title: good and easy - caramel popcorn
directions: Melt all the above in sauce pan on stove - DO NOT BURN. Pour hot over 2 bags of popped natural microwave popcorn. Enjoy this watching TV.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown and salt hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle Chinese noodles over top and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: rosemary-garlic butter
directions: Whisk together until well combined.
Use with halibut dish or use to make garlic bread.

title: pinwheel tortillas
directions: Mix all of the filling ingredients together well. Divide the filling and spread evenly over tortillas.
Roll up tortillas. Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends.
Chill for approximately 3 hours.
Unwrap. Cut into slices 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick. Discard ends. Dip into salsa. Eat.

title: turnip greens
directions: Wash greens thoroughly.
Drain.
Tear into bite size pieces. Combine greens, bacon and water in a Dutch oven and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add vinegar, pepper flakes, salt and
pepper. Cover and cook an additional hour.
Remove bacon slices before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, frozen lemonade, juice and extract.
Mix well.
Freeze in gallon plastic jug. Don't fill to top.
Defrost 3 hours before serving.
Cut off top of jug; pour in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except whipped cream; mix well.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Cover; refrigerate. Yields ten 1/2-cup servings.

title: individual pizza rounds
directions: To make a thin crust for pizza, separate each pita into two round pizza crusts.
For a thicker crust, use 1 whole pita bread. Place bread, hollow side up, on baking sheet.
Spread equal amounts of green pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms or any of your favorite pizza ingredients.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham and cheese skillet supper
directions: Cut ham slices into strips 3/4-inch wide.
Cook cabbage in boiling salted water 10 minutes or until tender crisp; drain thoroughly.
Cook onion in oleo in large fry pan 2 minutes.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in ham strips and cabbage; cook slowly 10 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: melt-a-ways
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar in medium size bowl. Gradually add flour, mixing in thoroughly; stir in nuts.
Chill. Form teaspoonfuls of dough into marble size balls by rolling lightly between palms of hands.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in moderate 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until pale golden.
Remove from cookie sheet with spatula.
While still hot, roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Cool on wire cake rack.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine sauce and water in bowl.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, combine Ricotta, cottage, Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses, egg and nutmeg.

title: cinnamon logs
directions: Cut bread into 4 x 2 x 2-inch rectangular logs.
Let stand to dry slightly.
Blend milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and nutmeg in medium bowl.
Pour into shallow pan large enough to hold bread in 1 layer.
Arrange bread in milk mixture, turning to coat all sides.
Chill until liquid is absorbed, several hours or overnight.

title: skirt steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces about 3-inches square.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and paprika.
Heat oil/butter in heavy skillet (several tablespoons).
Quickly brown steak on both sides (do not overcook).
Into 1/2 cup water, add soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add this to the steak.
Shake and simmer for about 5 minutes.
(This last 5 minutes can be done just before serving to allow you to prepare it earlier.)
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, 6 tablespoons of the margarine and 1 cup of oats; mix until crumbly.
Save 1 cup of the crumbs for the top. To the remaining crumbs, add the egg and mix well.
Press this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, then pour a can of cherry pie filling on top.
To the 1 cup of crumbs, add 1/4 cup of oats and 2 tablespoons margarine, 1/2 cup nuts and 1/4 cup brown sugar; mix, then put over the cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (moderate).
Mix flour, baking powder, allspice and salt.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add egg whites; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in oats, applesauce and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 11 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool on rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: biscuit and chicken(serves 5)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rinse peas to separate.
Heat peas, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper to boiling, stirring frequently.
Prepare rolled biscuits as directed on package.
Pour hot chicken mixture into an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Place biscuits on cheese.
Bake until peas are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Form into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail jello cream
directions: Heat fruit and mix the jello in it.
Put in the refrigerator and let set a little.
Beat softened cream cheese and whipping cream together.
Fold the cream into the fruited jello and place back in refrigerator until it sets firmly.
Serves 6.

title: beulah mclellan's sweet potato pie
directions: Cream the potatoes until smooth.
Combine with next 8 ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: rumaki
directions: Cook bacon until partially cooked (browned, but still limp). Cut each slice in half and wrap around water chestnut and liver. Secure with toothpick.
In shallow dish, combine soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger, garlic powder and 1/4 cup water.
Add bacon/chicken livers and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Turn occasionally.
Remove from marinade and place on rack in shallow pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes, until browned and crispy.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter. Add flour and cook until smooth.
Add cream slowly.
Then cheese and seasonings.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Cook green beans in salted water.
Drain and mix with sauce.
Add water chestnuts and top with slivered, blanched toasted almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
(Can be made ahead, refrigerated, and then baked for 35 to 40 minutes.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour or cornstarch and brown in large skillet in a small amount of oil.
Add beef broth and simmer 15 minutes.

title: creamy chicken salad
directions: Dressing:
Shred the peel from the orange; peel and section orange over bowl to catch and reserve 1 teaspoon juice.
(Set aside sections.)
Combine peel, juice, yogurt, honey and poppy seed.
Cover and chill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan, combine the chicken, 1/2 cup of milk, sour cream and soup and bring to a boil.
Spoon mixture into 6 ungreased 10-ounce casserole dishes or custard cups or pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: sweet potato raisin patties
directions: Boil and mash sweet potatoes; add egg, salt and flour (if mixture is real moist).
Blend in raisins.
Drop tablespoons of mixture on heated greased frypan.
Brown slowly on both sides. Makes about 12 patties.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Stir together flour, sugar and baking soda and cut in shortening.
Mix buttermilk and yeast water. Stir in flour mixture.	Knead 4 to 5 times.
Pat out to 1/4-inch thick.	Place closely together on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush melted butter on top.

title: jamaican jerk pork chops
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Pour the flour and jerk seasoning into a large plastic bag, seal and shake to mix.
Add the chops, two at a time, reseal and shake to coat. Brown chops in oil and place them on a plate.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup mix per cup of hot water.
May use more, if desired.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground
beef
and	drain.	Add rest of ingredients and let cook until desired texture.
Serve on buns.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in celery and onion. Add salt, pepper and lemon
juice. Add chopped shrimp.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate several hours before serving. May be served with Fritos, Doritos or crackers.
May be prepared 2 days in advance.
Makes 1 quart.

title: yani's chocolate pots de creme
directions: In a heavy small saucepan, combine light cream, chocolate and sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 10 minutes or until mixture comes to a full boil and thickens.
Gradually stir about half of the hot mixture into beaten egg yolks; return yolk mixture to saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into 4 or 6 pot de creme cups or small dessert dishes.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mrs. florence hooks' spoon bread
directions: Scald meal with boiling water, add salt.
Cool.
Add eggs, milk and melted butter or margarine.
Bake in buttered pan (square about 9 x 9-inch) at 450° until browned (about 30 minutes).
Good warmed over.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Heat 2 to 3 minutes on High in microwave.
Mix.
Place by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: blueberry boy bait
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder, salt, butter, milk and eggs.
Blend at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened, then beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Arrange blueberries on top.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: orange sunbeam cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine until fine.
Stir in raisins, chopped. Blend egg, orange rind, orange juice and sweetener.
Sprinkle over mixture, stirring with a fork until it holds together.
Shape dough into balls, using a teaspoonful for each. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Pour butter over nuts, coating well.
Single layer on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle salt.
Bake for 1 hour at 275°.
Stir often.

title: "sin"
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts until crumbly and spread on bottom of 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and the sugar.
Spread on top of crust.
Mix pudding and milk and pour onto cream cheese layer.
Chill 2 hours.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: eggplant au gratin
directions: Peel and boil eggplant in salted water until soft; strain off water and mash.
Fry onions in butter.
Beat eggs.
Grate cheese. Combine all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Dot with butter; cover with crackers.
Return to oven; cook 10 minutes.
(May use potato chips, crushed, for topping.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide recipe mixture into 3 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into middle comes out dry and clean.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Pour hot water over sugar, salt and shortening in large mixer bowl; let cool. Beat eggs; add 3 cups flour and mix all together with mixer.
Add 3 more cups flour; mix by hand.
Refrigerate overnight, covered with towel.
Punch down and knead; make into rolls.
(Divide dough into halves and roll out and cut.)
Let rise 3 to 4 hours, then bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pasta carbonara(serves 4 to 6.)
directions: Saute bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Boil 4 quarts water in a large pot.
Add 2 teaspoons salt and then drop in spaghetti.
Stir with wooden spoon and return to boil.
Cook until tender, about 8 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs thoroughly in large bowl suitable for serving.
Have cooked bacon and chopped parsley ready at hand.
When pasta is done, drain immediately in colander.
Pour hot spaghetti into bowl of eggs and immediately begin tossing.
As the strands of pasta become coated with beaten eggs, their heat will cook the eggs.
Sprinkle on bacon and chopped parsley.
Toss again and serve immediately.
Top with Parmesan cheese and black pepper.

title: cheese and sour cream enchilada
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add taco seasoning and green chilies to meat.
